title: angel delight
directions: Melt chocolate; cool.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.
Add sugar, pecans and whipped whipping cream.
Break cake in pan into chunks and pour mixture over cake.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Roll dough in hands to make a ball, place each ball on cookie sheet.
Dip rim of small glass in butter, then sugar and press on each cookie to flatten.
I use cookie press dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: jan's famous red beans and rice
directions: Pour beans into large pot.
Fill one empty can with water and add.
Add onions, Worcestershire, garlic, sliced meat, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until beans thicken and mixture is "pasty."
Serve over salted rice.
Season with Tabasco to taste. Serve with Mexican cornbread.

title: lorene staggs' chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter with Crisco.
Add sugar and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift in flour; add cocoa, salt and baking powder, adding gradually along with flour mixture and milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake on middle rack of oven at 300°, in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in salt, pepper and flour.
Stir until smooth; cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and chicken soup.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens; add broccoli and mushrooms.
Cook until broccoli is done.
Serves 6.
Also good with cauliflower instead of broccoli.

title: orange julius - dee's way
directions: Put all ingredients into blender, except ice.
Blend to mix. Add 6 ice cubes.
Blend until gone.
Check slushiness of drink. Add ice cubes as needed to make drink as thick as you like.
We like ours real thick.
Pour into tumblers and serve.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Melt and spread over Rice Krispies.

title: chicken and green chile casserole
directions: In a large pan, combine broth, soup, chiles and chicken.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Tear tortillas into quarters and add chicken to mixture.
Lightly grease your casserole dish.
Place 1/2 torn tortillas on bottom of pan.
Then place 1/2 mixture over tortillas.
Repeat again with torn tortillas, then the rest of chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Simmer onion in bacon drippings.
Add paprika and water; bring to boil.
Add cut-up chicken and simmer 45 minutes or until all water is absorbed and chicken is lightly browned.

title: enchilada squares
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain excess fat off.
Spread beef in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Beat together the eggs, milk, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce mix; pour over meat.
Sprinkle with sliced olives; top with corn chips.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed winter squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Place squash halves, cut side down, in a shallow baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until almost tender.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add other ingredients, except flour. Add flour slowly.
Spoon into muffins pans and let rise 60 to 90 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions; using a 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Cool cake on a wire rack. Meanwhile, prepare pudding according to package directions; pour pudding into a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Tear cake into small pieces and gently push down into the pudding. Drizzle with 3/4 cup of chocolate syrup. Spread with whipped topping. Drizzle with remaining chocolate syrup. Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate until serving.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix together zucchini and onion.
Sprinkle Bisquick over zucchini.
Mix together eggs, oil, Parmesan cheese, parsley, marjoram, salt, pepper, oregano and fried bacon (optional).
Add egg mixture to zucchini mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 12-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: baked oysters(served each christmas at my friend sandy's home)
directions: Mix together crumbs and butter; set aside.
Mix oysters, liquid, cream, salt and pepper.
Layer oyster mix with crumbs in two layers.
Sprinkle each layer with nutmeg and parsley if desired.
Cover top layer with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 425° to 450°.

title: snow drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Begin adding sugar gradually and continue until whites are stiff.
Add vanilla. Gently fold in chopped nuts and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Place cookies in a preheated oven at 350°. Close oven door and turn oven off.
Leave cookies in oven for 3 hours or overnight.
Makes a firm cookie which stays white.
Makes about 50.

title: mozzarella chicken breasts
directions: Season meat, then place in skillet with oil and garlic.
Cover skillet and cook until meat is done.
Remove lid and brown chicken.
Remove chicken and add onions, peppers and mushrooms to skillet and saute.
Return chicken to skillet and add wine.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Then add cheese and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order above.
Refrigerate for three to four hours. Add bacon bits just before serving.

title: sausage and egg casserole(for breakfast or brunch)
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
This dish can be frozen after cooking, then heated for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: icebox cookie squares
directions: Layer plain graham crackers in bottom of jelly roll pan (cookie sheet type).
Mix together and cook until thick 1 egg, milk, sugar and 2 sticks margarine.
Take off heat and add to 1 cup cracker crumbs, 1 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Mix with first mixture well, then spread over layered crackers, then add another layer of graham crackers.

title: coconut date dreams
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except Rice Krispies, and boil for 4
minutes, stirring constantly. Add Rice Krispies. Shape into balls and roll in coconut. Makes 2 dozen.

title: spring radish and cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Sprinkle with salt; cover and chill several hours.
Drain cucumbers well.
Combine with radishes.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend into cucumbers and radishes.
If desired, pile mixture into the center of a tomato aspic ring.
Dust with a little ground pepper.
May also be served on lettuce leaves.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: *Can substitute 1 cup evaporated milk with 2 teaspoons of vinegar added for the sour cream.
A penny saved is a penny earned.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Trim and wash cauliflower leaving head intact.
Cook until just barely done.
Do not overcook.
Drain upside down in colander.
Invert casserole over colander and turn so cauliflower is right side up in casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted and sauce is thick.
Pour sauce over cauliflower and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve from casserole or transfer carefully to serving dish.
Sprinkle with snipped chives.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from baking pan immediately.

title: tomato bread
directions: Mix butter and garlic.
Place in fridge to chill and bring back to room temperature.
Can be made a day in advance.
Slice bread lengthwise.
Spread garlic butter on bread.
Place tomatoes across bread.
Cover tomatoes with cheese.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Broil at 400°.
Cut in slices and serve hot.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Add and mix rest of ingredients, except chicken.
Lay chicken breasts in rice and liquid mixture; cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: curry dip
directions: Stir all together and store in refrigerator.
Keeps well. Serve with fresh vegetables for dipping. Excellent with cauliflower.

title: zucchini and pasta supper dish
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add minced garlic and stir-fry until garlic just begins to turn brown.
Add zucchini and onion and saute over medium heat until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, salt, basil, oregano and pepper; cover and cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and let sit for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Toss spaghetti with butter and Parmesan cheese; arrange on a large platter (heated if possible).
Top with vegetable mixture and serve immediately. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Combine pudding with 3 cups cold milk; beat 2 minutes.
Set until thickened.
Fold in Cool whip.
Place layer of graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread layer of pudding, then crackers.
Top off with crackers.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix altogether.
For 1 cup of hot chocolate, put 3 tablespoons of mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: spoon bread(s. carolina)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine water and cornmeal; bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cook and stir until very thick, about 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, corn, margarine, onion powder and garlic powder.
Stir until cheese melts and mixture is smooth. Stir in milk.

title: crab soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Add celery and cook for 3 minutes.
Add flour and stir over low heat until frothy.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes.
Stir often to prevent scorching.
Add Tabasco sauce. Gradually stir in milk.
Increase heat and bring to a boil. Reduce immediately so it simmers.
Add crab meat; return to simmer and cook about 3 minutes until crab meat is hot.
Stir in scallions.

title: wine and provoli chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter and cook until done.

title: turkish coffee
directions: Pour water into a brass coffee pot or saucepan and add sugar; bring to boil.
Add coffee and cardamon (optional) stirring constantly.
When mixture comes to a boil and becomes frothy, remove from fire and stir until froth has receded.
Repeat this process two more times.
After third time, pour into demitasse cups or small cups.

title: saucy squash
directions: Wash fresh squash and cut into small pieces.
Cut onion into same size pieces (approximate).
Chop pepper into small pieces. Cut up tomatoes or puree in blender, if desired.
Place all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together.
Makes a large serving.

title: grilled cayenne chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
Combine mayonnaise, garlic powder, lime juice, salt and cayenne in a shallow bowl; stir well.
Place chicken on grill rack.
Coat well with sauce.
Grill chicken for about 5 minutes; turn.
Brush with remaining sauce.
Broil chicken until juices run clear when meat is pierced with a knife, about 10 minutes longer.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Cook stir-fry vegetables according to package.
Combine and mix pasta and vegetables together.
Stir in Italian dressing; add other ingredients and stir.
Can season with garlic, Parmesan cheese, etc.
Can also add cooked chicken tenders or beef if desired.
To avoid dryness, you may add olive oil (1 to 2 tablespoons) as desired.

title: homemade sausage 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry a small amount to test for seasoning.
Add more salt if necessary.
Form into small patties, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Fry in a heavy pan, browning on both sides, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for several hours.

title: frozen jello punch
directions: Combine Jell-O and sugar in large bowl.
Add 1 quart boiling water; mix well.
Add 1 quart cold water, lemon juice and pineapple juice; mix well.
Pour into 1-gallon freezer container. Freeze until firm.
Thaw until slushy.
Place in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Yields 40 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add brown sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add enough powdered sugar for the consistency you want, thicker for a cake. If you like maple flavor, you can use maple flavoring in the icing; otherwise, use vanilla.
Dip marshmallows in melted butter. Roll in the sugar-cinnamon mixture and place on wide end of the crescent roll.
Fold wide ends over marshmallows, then roll it up to the point end.
Pinch edges together well.
Place in greased muffin pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool about 5 minutes, then remove and place on wax paper.
Put icing and nuts on, if you desire.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in pie shell for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 pies.

title: easy and elegant beef stew
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Put into it beef (do not brown the meat first), carrots, soup, bay leaf, potatoes, 1/2 cup wine and onions.
Cover and bake in 275° oven for 4 hours.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water, stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in pineapple, pie filling and 1/2 cup pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork until smooth. Stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green peppers, onion and seasonings; roll in nuts. Garnish plate with pineapple rings and parsley sprigs. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: shrimp with artichokes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in half and half and milk.
Add parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened; set aside.
Arrange artichoke hearts and shrimp in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with mushroom sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven candied sweet potatoes
directions: Clean and cook whole sweet potatoes in water just until tender.
Drain, peel and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half each of the potatoes, brown sugar, butter and salt.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until glazed.
Sprinkle cinnamon and then marshmallows over top.
Bake about 5 minutes longer or until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat milk and egg; blend in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt to form batter.
Holding your finger over bottom of funnel, fill with batter.
Hold funnel as near oil as possible (oil in deep fryer or frying pan heated to 375°).
Drop batter into oil in a circular movement from center outward.
Fry until puffy and golden brown, turning once.
Remove; place on paper towel.
Sift confectioners sugar on cakes.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 dozen 3-inch cakes.

title: home baked beans
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Cover with 3 inches of water and allow to soak overnight.
In the morning, add salt and soda and bring to a boil.
Cook for 1/2 hour or until tender.
More water should be added if the beans become dry.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole and add the remaining ingredients.
Bacon should be fried very crisp and crumbled before adding.
Bacon drippings may be added for additional flavor.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, keeping covered with liquid.
Recipe may be halved.

title: play dough - cooked
directions: Mix and cook over low heat until thickened and hard to stir. Add coloring.
Mix in.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat the milk, pudding and orange juice.
Stir in sour cream. Serve fresh pineapple, apple slices, bananas and mandarin oranges.

title: sugar-free light and easy fun cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Next, mix wet items.
Quickly combine all ingredients, placed in oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Mix well; add chicken and simmer 5 minutes in saucepan.
Add 99 cent size bag Doritos. Mix well and put in large baking dish. Cover with 3/4 pound grated American or Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well everything except egg whites.
Add the unbeaten whites and beat well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's fruit cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box in a large bowl. Drain juice from sliced pineapple and cherries into cake mix. Add crushed pineapple. Mix well. In a separate bowl put self-rising flour. Take mixed fruit, chopped pecans, raisins, chopped cherries and mince meat and add to self-rising flour. Coat with flour, then gently fold into cake mix. Put into pans sprayed with Pam. Bake for approximately 1 hour
in a preheated 350° oven. After 1 hour turn oven down to 200° and cook for several hours or until you can stick an ice pick in and it comes out clean.

title: chicken with wine and mushrooms
directions: Lightly coat chicken with bread crumbs.
Saute garlic in butter in a frying pan, then add chicken and cook on low until chicken is cooked.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Put flour and water mixture in frying pan to make gravy.
Add bouillon and just enough Gravy Master to add color.

title: candied apples sauce
directions: Boil until red hots melt.
Quarter 3 unpeeled apples and core. Cook in mixture until tender.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Combine milk and cream; heat to boiling point.
Add and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes (as for mashed potatoes).
Cut bacon into small bits and fry.
Remove from grease.
Cook carrot, celery and onion in bacon grease.
Remove from grease.
Combine all ingredients into a large pan and simmer for a few minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Starting with sauce, cover bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Then put 1/3 noodles, 1/2 browned meat, 1/2 egg slices, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese, 1/2 the pepper and 1/2 of the Ricotta cheese.

title: herbed squash
directions: Slice squash thinly.
Saute squash in oleo until tender, but not mushy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well until heated through.
Serves 4.
Contains 99 calories and 2.4 g fat per serving.

title: easy cheese lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
Spray 11x7 inch baking dish with non-stick cooking spray.
Spread 1/3 of the sauce on bottom of pan, arrange 3 noodles in single layer over sauce.
Top with another 1/3 of the sauce, all of the ricotta cheese and vegetables, and 1/2 of mozzarella cheese, then remaining noodles in single layer.
Spread evenly with remaining sauce.

title: macaroni-cabbage fry
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Stir in cabbage, onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender. Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Toss hot macaroni with cabbage.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Heat on low for 5 minutes.
Just before serving, top with remaining cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Stir sugar, water, vanilla and food coloring until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil.
Insert a candy thermometer and cook until it registers to 234° (or the soft ball stage).
During this stage, keep the heat around medium or medium-high.
When the correct temperature is reached, remove from heat and add butter. Stir well and pour over popped corn (a large bowl will do).
Stir with a wooden spoon; then turn out onto waxed paper to cool.

title: norwegian butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Beat until light.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Work in nuts.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Press piece of candied peel into dough. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: two flavor bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line two 9-inch square pans with aluminum foil.
Combine 3 cups flour, 2/3 cup of the sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt in a food processor and whir until well mixed.
Cut 1/2 pound of the butter into small pieces and add to the flour mixture. Pulse until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With a fork, beat 1 of the eggs with 1 tablespoon water and the almond extract.
With the motor running, pour egg mixture into food processor and whir just until large crumbs start to form.
Remove 1 cup of the crumbs and set aside.
Pulse remaining mixture until it forms a ball.
Divide dough in half and press half into the bottom of each prepared pan. Bake 1 pan until top starts to look dry, about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Spread jam over dough in the other pan, leaving a 1/8-inch edge.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake until golden brown, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Using a 4-quart saucepan or pot, blend eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add milk, then add water; stir to blend.
Double boil until custard has thickened, about 40 minutes.
Let cool, then pour into a 1 gallon freezer (electric or hand crank).
Add vanilla flavor.
Freeze until it becomes firm.
Makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt, chocolate and corn syrup in saucepan.
Cook and store over low heat until sugar dissolves. Cook slowly to soft ball stage (238°).
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; cool mixture to 110° or lukewarm.
Beat in vanilla and nuts for 3 minutes or until mixture is not glossy. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix all together well and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in a little ball and press out with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: flowerpot herb cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, garlic, basil and dill. Mix well. Put in small flowerpot. Sprinkle pepper on top to look like soil. Stick fresh dill or basil in to look like they are growing.

title: easy pizza
directions: Put buns on pizza pan.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons pizza sauce on buns and cover with cheese.
Heat in
microwave 10 to 15 seconds.

title: boiled candy
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, 1/2 teaspoon cocoa and oats.
Dip onto wax paper.
(If you like you can add some peanut butter, nuts or coconut.)

title: chewies
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Melt (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add flour and stir in well (may use mixer).
Then add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Place pared 1/4-inch carrot chunks, diced onion and cubed potato (these may be unpeeled) in chicken broth.
Add lemon, nutmeg and other seasonings to the broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes, covered, or until vegetables are tender.
Puree in a blender.
Add a cup of milk.

title: grandma's tamale pie
directions: Put chili in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cooked macaroni.
Boil water and stir in corn meal to make mush.
Put mush on top of macaroni.
Top with grated cheese and olives.

title: celery-apple salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice on apples as they are cut.
Mix apples, celery, walnuts and 15 to 20 grapes.
Make dressing of mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar; pour over apple and celery mixture.
Mix until covered.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Combine yogurt, lemon juice and oregano.
Marinate chicken in mixture for about 2 hours.
Saute minced garlic and chicken in pan until cooked.
Crumble cheese on top and serve.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Stir together sugar with ReaLemon juice.
Prick top of baked bread with fork and pour lemon juice and sugar mixture over evenly.
Leave in pan for 25 minutes.
Makes two loaves.

title: easy and delicious banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork; stir in all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rigatoni salad
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients in a saucepan; heat until sugar dissolves completely, then cool.
Add oil.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Keeps well.

title: date pudding
directions: Combine dates, water and soda.
Mix well.
When cool, add butter, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin pan (biscuits-uncooked).
Mix all other ingredients except cheese into the meat.
Fill biscuit half way with meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake according to biscuit directions.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook
Minute
rice
according to directions on box.
In separate
skillet;
fry
sausage,
diced
onions,
diced green pepper and mushrooms together until sausage is browned and the onions and
pepper are tender.
Then take off stove; drain off excess grease
and then mix sausage, onions, green peppers and mushrooms in with your rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan; bring to a slow boil and let mixture boil until the soft ball stage of 234° is reached. Remove from stove; add remaining ingredients and beat until creamy.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Allow this to cool slightly before cutting in squares.
This saves nicely if refrigerated in a covered container.

title: easy fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter in saucepan until mixture forms soft ball.
Stir in chocolate chips; pour quickly onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add both soups, sour cream and corn.
Mix with noodles.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked barley and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute barley, in 2 tablespoons butter in skillet, over medium heat, for about 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: light cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cottage cheese, Egg Beaters and sugar until smooth.
Add cream cheese, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Continue to beat until smooth and creamy.
Line a muffin pan with 12 cup cake liners. Place 1 vanilla wafer in each cup.
Spoon cream cheese mixture on top of vanilla wafers.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until set.
Top with pie filling.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear cake into small bite size pieces.
Place in medium serving dish.
(This dish should be half full, no more than 3/4 full.)
Mix strawberries and glaze.
Spoon over cake pieces.
Cover with whip topping.
Cover dish and chill until ready to serve.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pans for about 15 minutes.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all together; place on lettuce leaves.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix cake according to box instructions.
Add oil and vanilla. Stir in pecans, bananas and pineapple.
Spoon batter in 2 cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: pineapple coconut pecan cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, soda and pineapple well with beaten eggs. Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rudi lechner's chicken soup (from the houston chronicle food pages)
directions: Wash hen; remove giblets and split hen into quarters.
Place in large pot; add water to cover.
Add carrots, celery, onion, garlic, parsley, salt, worcestershire and peppercorns.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours, removing grease and foam with a ladle while cooking.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and enjoy with your favorite fruits, sliced.

title: seasoned jerky
directions: Make a marinade with the onion powder, black pepper, soy sauce, seasoned salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Soak the meat strips in it. Refrigerate overnight. Stir
a couple of times while marinating. Drain meat and dry.

title: microwave chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, tomato, onions, green pepper and garlic powder in 16-ounce casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 1 minute; stir.
Cover tightly and microwave until hot, 1 to 2 minutes longer; drain.

title: taco chicken
directions: Put chicken in 2-quart saucepan; add just enough water to cover. Boil until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove chicken from broth, but keep broth. Cut chicken into chunks.

Crumble 1/2 of chips in bottom of long casserole. Put chicken chunks on chips. Mix soup with 1 soup can broth and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with onion and peppers. Add other 1/2 of chips. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Add buttermilk and salt, then flour.
Mix well and pour in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add coconut or nuts if desired.

title: popcorn balls(kids recipe)
directions: Melt caramels with water over low heat, stirring until smooth. Pour over popped corn.
Toss until well coated.
With hands slightly moistened with cold water, form into balls.
Makes 6 balls.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Combine bourbon, catsup, sugar, onion, Worcestershire and hot sauce in saucepan.
Simmer uncovered for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cut franks into 5 to 6 sections.
Add franks to sauce and simmer for an additional 1/2 hour.
Serve hot as appetizer with toothpicks.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Dice orange slice candies.
Combine with pecans, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour and mix.
Set aside.
Cream oleo with brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift together flour and salt; add to the mixing bowl and blend well. Fold in orange and nut mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 270°; cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs; add milk and shortening. Sift remaining ingredients together, add to egg mixture and beat well.
Pour into greased shallow 9 x 9-inch pan and bake in hot oven until bread shrinks from sides of pan, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Use wire whisk.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: creamy chicken hash
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook onion until tender, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in half and half; cook, stirring, until thickened.
Stir potatoes and chicken into mixture.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover skillet and simmer about 10 minutes, or until mixture is heated through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine dry ingredients;
cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Turn dough out onto floured surface, and kneed 1 or 2 times. Lightly roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness (17 1/2 x 8 inch rectangle).
Sprinkle sausage evenly over dough.
Roll dough jellyroll fashion, starting at long end.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices and place on greased cookie sheets.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms on paper towels.
Remove and chop stems.
Fry stems in olive oil in a nonstick fry pan.
When stems are sauteed, add and stir in bread crumbs; add cheese.
Cool a little for handling and with a teaspoon fill the mushroom cavities with bread crumb mixture.
Place stuffed mushrooms in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onion.
Cover with water and simmer.
Add vinegar, salt and sugar; cook until candied down a bit.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add water and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle chocolate bits on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Fold in apples and nuts last, after batter is mixed.

title: donna's homemade, mouth-watering, lip-smacking, toe-tapping rolls
directions: Pour water into a large bowl and sprinkle yeast over water. Add sugar and powdered milk.
Let this mixture stand for 15 minutes (sponge method).
Mix in egg, salt, shortening and 2 cups of flour.
Mix additional flour in slowly until it pulls away from the bowl.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead until the dough springs back, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Place dough into a bowl and cover dough with approximately 1 teaspoon of oil; cover with a towel and place in a draft-free area (oven with the light on) and let rise until doubled in bulk.
After dough has doubled in bulk, punch down and dip shaped rolls in melted butter.
Let rolls rise again until doubled in bulk in a draft-free area (oven with the light on).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Brush tops of rolls with melted butter.
Enjoy! Enjoy!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Mix together.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins.
Bake approximately 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: spicy vegetable chili
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine soups and water.
Stir in chickpeas, black beans, zucchini, carrots, chili powder, thyme and pepper.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all but coconut by hand until blended.
Drop by teaspoon into the coconut.
Roll to coat; place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: water chestnut snacks
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat; add pepper and onion and cook until soft.
Add mushrooms, pepperoni and Italian seasoning.
Add spaghetti sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Cook until blended together.
Cook pasta as directed and add to sauce.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted at 350°, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips and sprinkle with lemon pepper seasoning and salt.
Pour dressing over chicken and let set for 1 hour.
Chicken can be rolled in flour and fried or can be baked in oven without flour at 350° until done.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand with lemon juice until thick.
Add pie cherries (drained well), pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Then fold in Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin patch bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then cream the sugar and pumpkin.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir all together.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.
Slice into bars, and serve.

title: party punch
directions: Pour juices and ginger ale in a punch bowl. Spoon in sherbet. Let stand about 20 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate. Make a large amount.

title: pink cake
directions: Dissolve lozenges in milk overnight.
Cream all together; fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stock(for low sodium diets)
directions: When boiling a chicken for a recipe, cook it in a deep boiler, cover with water, and add celery, carrots and parsley.
When chicken is tender, remove it, discard the vegetables and then strain the juices through cheese cloth to make a clear broth.
Let the broth sit overnight in the refrigerator, so any fat will come to the top.
Discard the fat and put the clear, clean broth into pint or quart size freezer bags for easy access when a recipe calls for chicken broth.
(Avoid using canned chicken stock in any of your recipes as most are high in sodium.)

title: party mix
directions: Mix together and bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: margie miller's strawberry jam
directions: Use any container 1 pint or smaller that has tight fitting lids.
Wash, scald and drain containers and lids, or use automatic dishwasher with hot rinse water.
Stem and crush strawberries one layer at a time.
Measure 1 3/4 cups fruit exactly.
Place in larger bowl or pan.
Thoroughly mix sugar with fruit.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine lemon juice and fruit pectin.
Stir into fruit.
Continue stirring about 3 minutes.
Ladle quickly into containers.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours to set.
Store in freezer.
Will keep 2 or 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 cups of jam.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix grated cheese with Bisquick and sausage.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: onion bread
directions: Saute onions in margarine and set aside.
Mix Bisquick, milk, egg and cheese, then add onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: beef log
directions: Mix all together.
Form, shape and roll in pecans.
Let blend overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger and add seasoning mix, tomatoes, corn and olives.
Heat mixture through, stirring to blend ingredients. Prepare corn bread mix following directions on package, but adding caraway and/or pepper flakes.
Spoon corn bread mixture into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spoon corn bread mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy drop danish
directions: Mix baking mix, margarine and sugar until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough forms; beat 15 strokes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make a shallow well in center of each with back of spoon; fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake until golden, 10 to 15 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with glaze.

title: keith's fruit salad
directions: Drain all cans of fruit.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Mix in Cool Whip (thawed). In a large bowl, mix fruit and cream cheese mixture together. Add pecans and mix together. Cover and put in refrigerator for about 1 hour or until firm.

title: foil roasted chicken
directions: Line a roasting pan with a large piece of foil.
Place vegetables in foil and arrange chicken on top.
Empty can of tomatoes over all and season with salt and pepper.
Wrap foil around chicken tightly.
Roast at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn back foil and baste chicken with pan juices.
Brush chicken with margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Roast 45 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: three cheese chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Remove vegetables and set aside.

title: plain white cake(1 egg cake)
directions: Combine.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) greased pans for about 25 to 30 minutes at 365°.

title: jello eggs
directions: Save empty egg shells until you have desired amount.
Empty shell by making small hole in end of egg (only big enough to get all the egg out) and rinse thoroughly.
Collect and save in cold water in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make various flavors of Jello enough to fill eggs.
Funnel Jello into eggs and place in refrigerator to harden.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into balls. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: german cabbage chowder
directions: Brown the sausage; add butter, carrots and caraway seed.
Cook until tender.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cook slowly for about 10 minutes until the cabbage is tender.
Makes 8 cups.

title: crusty pintos
directions: Saute onions and peppers in hot oil over medium heat, about 4 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add chili powder and cumin and cook an other 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, Tabasco, salt and 3 tablespoons parsley.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour bean mixture into pan and spread evenly.
Combine cheese and crushed tortilla chips to make an even layer on top of beans.
(If prepared ahead, cover and refrigerate at this point.
Remove cover before baking.)
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until hot and cheese has melted to form a crust.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley before serving.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue ham sandwiches
directions: In 10-inch skillet, saute onions in butter over medium heat until tender.
Add ketchup, water, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce and stir until well blended.
Add chipped ham 1 to 2 slices at a time until well mixed.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry bread(delicious!!)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and pour in oil, eggs and strawberries without juice.
Mix.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese with small amount of berry juice and serve as spread.

title: sinful brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix together.
Then spoon cream cheese mixture on top and stir through cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 325° in glass pan for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli; cut into pieces.
Cut chestnuts into small strips.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli and water chestnuts.
Toss.
Refrigerate before using.

title: meatball soup
directions: In large pot, heat broth to simmer.
Meanwhile, mix beef, eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape into meatballs and drop into broth. Cut up onions, slice celery and carrots, shred cabbage and cut tomatoes in eights.

title: heavenly pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour.
Cool cake 10 minutes in pan before removing to rack.
Cool completely before serving.

title: sunday spice cake
directions: In mixing bowl, put flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, Crisco, cloves, nutmeg, allspice, molasses and milk.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder and soda.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Slice squash and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sausage balls with cheese dip
directions: Roll sausage into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls; bake in oven on broiler pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
(This drains the grease as it cooks.)
In crock-pot, melt Velveeta cheese.
Add chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes and cooked sausage balls.
Mix thoroughly and serve with toothpicks.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Put cinnamon and sugar in plastic bag, along with a few pieces of biscuit; shake until coated.
Repeat until all are coated.
Place coated pieces of biscuit in a bundt pan.
Put remaining sugar and cinnamon in saucepan with butter; cook until boiling, stirring constantly. Pour over biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: carolina cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan, well-greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Ice, if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Chill.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: vote for chili "c"(winning entry of "7th annual chili cookoff"-spanish iii)
directions: Cook hamburg in frying pan.
In another pot, cook onions.
When hamburg is cooked, add to onions.
Then add rest of ingredients. Let it simmer for a while.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
Prick pie shell with fork. Bake until lightly browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Place pie shell on rack to cool completely.
Place 1/2 of the cheese in baked pie shell.
Top evenly with sausage, mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Spread on remaining cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over filled pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: shamrock mint freeze
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid in medium saucepan. Stir gelatin into syrup and let rest 5 minutes to soften.
Place over moderate heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add mint jelly and cook, stirring until jelly is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in pineapple.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate or stir over ice water until mixture thickens slightly.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk, egg, vanilla and cinnamon.
Melt stick of butter in casserole dish.
Pour mixture over butter.
Spoon peaches and juice on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine beef, onions, celery and carrots in a large casserole dish.
Mix salt, sugar, tapioca, tomato juice and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture.
Add diced potatoes after 2 hours cooking. Total cook time is 4 to 5 hours at 250°.

title: dutch gooey cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg and butter (melted).
This makes a stiff dough.
Pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend together 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar (leaving out 1/8 cup of sugar to sprinkle on top).
Pour over dough and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red apple inn chicken
directions: Pepper, but do not salt, the chicken breasts.
Put bacon strips on top of chicken.
Place layer of dried beef (not corned beef) in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange bacon wrapped chicken on beef rounds.
Cover with mixture of chicken soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Place in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
When tender, remove foil and let brown slightly. Serve on bed of rice.
Makes 12 portions.

title: kourabiedes 3
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add	yolk
and vanilla.
Mix well. Add
sifted
dry
ingredients.
Shape into crescents on floured board.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Do not brown.
Allow to cool and sift powdered sugar on top.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Blend sugar and cream cheese.
In separate bowl blend Cool Whip, pudding and milk.
Fold into first mixture.
Flowerpot should be lined with foil.
Alternate 1 inch cookie crumbs and 1 inch mixture of pudding; end with cookie crumbs on top.
Decorate with bouquet.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put milk and butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Let margarine melt.
Add vanilla, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to a boil. Remove from stove and add Quick oats.
Stir and place by tablespoon drops on wax paper.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine spinach or broccoli, soup, cheese (except for the 1/2 cup for top) and sour cream.
Heat well on stove top.
Fold potatoes and ham into mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes; 50 to 55 minutes if using fresh potatoes.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix together and spread over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 4 pieces (with or without peel).
Place in baking dish, then add margarine, onion slices, green pepper, picante hot sauce.
Let potatoes bake until soft.
Bring out of oven and sprinkle Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese, put back in oven and heat until cheese is melted over potatoes.
Serve hot.

title: arroz con pollo(rice with chicken, panama food)
directions: Seasoning chicken to taste; brown chicken, no flour.
After browning chicken, dice your onion and bell pepper.
In that same pot with chicken, add the olives, capers, pimientos, turmeric, onion, bell pepper, black pepper, salt and onion powder.
Leave all the juices in the olives, capers and pimientos.
Add 3 cups water. Let it cook on medium heat until water cooks down for rice, then add rice and let it cook until rice is done.

title: banana slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add remaining ingredients, except beverage.
Freeze.
Thaw for 2 to 3 hours before serving time. Mix with potato masher; add beverage.
Serve thick.
Makes 75 to 100 servings.

title: spicy sausage and potato casserole
directions: Butter 2-quart casserole.
Arrange first 4 ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Beat together next 4 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over first mixture. Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Drizzle with sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake additional 10 minutes.

title: sea scallops with tomatoes and shallot butter
directions: Core and peel tomatoes.
Halve them crosswise.
Squeeze the halves gently to extract seeds; cut halves into 1/4-inch cubes. In a nonstick skillet large enough to hold scallops in 1 layer, heat oil and butter over high
heat.
When hot, add scallops, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring and shaking the pan and turning scallops, until lightly brown, about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle shallots, thyme and tomatoes evenly over scallops.
Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice and cook, stirring, for another minute.
Sprinkle with parsley, stir well and serve immediately.
Do not overcook.
Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, but omit salt.
Drain well.
Place broccoli in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg until well blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine oleo and bread crumbs and sprinkle over broccoli mixture. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, or until crumbs are light brown.

title: quick tomato-pepper sauce
directions: In a blender or food processor, whirl the sweet red pepper, onion, tomato sauce and red pepper sauce fo 2 minutes or until smooth.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
add egg yolks which have been well beaten.
Add flour, vanilla and pineapple.	Pour into pie shell and bake
minutes
or
until firm.
Beat egg whites; add 5 tablespoons
sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on pie and brown.

title: ambrosia spread
directions: Set aside 3 orange sections for garnish.
Chop remaining orange sections; set aside.
Stir together cream cheese, coconut and almonds until smooth.
Fold in chopped oranges.
Arrange reserved orange sections on top.
Chill.
Serve spread with assorted fruit breads and muffins.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Make balls with the first 10 ingredients.
Brown in oil; remove balls and stir in remaining ingredients.
Return meat to gravy.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix in eggs and flavorings.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour cherries in baking dish. Spread pineapple over cherries and cake mix over pineapple.
Pat down lightly. Slice margarine and place evenly over top to cover. Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: no-mix meat loaf
directions: Do not mix soups in with meat.
You must layer each ingredient.
Place meat in pan.
Put mushroom or potato soup on top of meat.
Add dried onion soup to meat.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.

title: my grandmother's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over oats and butter.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Sift the dry
ingredients and pour into the oat mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into 9 x 13-inch pan, then dump cherry pie filling, then dump dry cake mix on top.
Pour margarine evenly over everything.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all ingredients together, except cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Stir in eggs, milk and shortening into flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Peel onions and slice thin.
Separate into rings and dip into batter.
Drop rings into deep hot fat.
Do not crowd in pan.
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grape salad
directions: Let cream
cheese
and Cool Whip soften.
If grapes are large, cut in quarters, if small, halves.	Add all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix water, soda and cocoa together.
Add flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add milk and sugar; mix rest of ingredients with a little milk.
Add to milk in pan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
This can be used for any cream pie. Pour mixture into baked pie shell.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour (almost burnt) in bacon drippings.
Brown onion and bell pepper (lightly) in another pan.
Combine and add tomatoes and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly 45 minutes, then add seafood.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle gumbo file on top (about 1 tablespoon) and cook slowly 30 more minutes longer if preferred.

title: cheese stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash and scoop out centers of the tomatoes.
Retain the cap. Season.
Combine the cheese, cream, eggs and parsley in a bowl and mix.
Fill the tomatoes and sprinkle bread crumbs.
Replace the caps and place in a buttered baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 17 minutes.
Serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to full boil.
Boil 5 minutes until thermometer is 234°.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, vanilla and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well; put in refrigerator.

title: fern's texas pralines
directions: In a large pot mix buttermilk, sugar and baking soda.
Stir mixture until sugar is completely dissolved.
Then place pot on low to medium heat and let it boil to softball stage, stirring constantly.
Soft ball stage means dipping a spoon into candy and letting a small amount drip into cool water.
If you can form a soft ball with your fingers, it is ready.
Remove candy mixture from heat once soft ball stage is reached.
Then add pecan halves, vanilla and butter.
Beat mixture briskly until it is glossy. Quickly spoon onto greased wax paper.
If you like and have the time before the candy hardens, you can turn the pecan halves right side up.
Makes the patties look prettier.

title: brunch for "8"
directions: Mix bread, cheese and seafood. Spread over bottom of pan. Pour liquid on top (egg mixture)
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (crunchier) or 300° for 1 3/4 hours (softer). Serve with fresh fruit slices and pound cake.
Use the optional but tasty Cheese Sauce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and juice.
Place in refrigerator.
When Jell-O starts to set, add apples and nuts.
Mold, if desired, and chill for about 5 hours before serving.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually mix in milk and butter; add vanilla. Pour batter into a 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Sprinkle mixture from step 2 evenly over batter then pour 1-1/4 cups hot water over top. Do Not Stir.

title: buttermilk pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Soften margarine and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar gradually. Add oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, coconut and nuts.
Bake in 3 small or 2 regular loaf pans that have been greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour.

title: luscious coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Make two 9-inch layers.
When cooled, split both layers.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter and chocolate squares over low heat.
Remove from heat and add brown sugar.
In mixing bowl, beat egg and white sugar.
Gradually pour over melted chocolate mixture. Blend in baking powder, salt and flour.
Add vanilla and zucchini; mix 30 seconds.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be frosted or served plain.

title: perfection pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Blend in shortening until pea size lumps appear.
Blend egg and liquids.
Make a dough that is soft, but easy to handle.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt
butter
and
cocoa.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla. Mix well by hand.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for
to 40 minutes.
Place marshmallows on cake as soon as it
is
removed from oven.	Combine confectioners sugar, milk, cocoa, margarine and vanilla and drizzle over marshmallows.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Chop vegetables fine.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add well drained vegetables, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Serve on snack crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well, forcing out liquid.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 8 hours prior to serving.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together three times.
Blend in eggs and oil on low speed of mixer.
Add applesauce and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm on top and toothpick comes out clean.
When cool, remove from pan and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: majestic layered spinach salad
directions: Layer spinach, eggs, mushrooms and Swiss cheese in 2-quart bowl.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and sugar in bowl.
Stir in green onions.
Spread over salad, sealing to edge.
Chill, covered, for several hours to overnight.
Top with bacon before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Add chicken broth until consistency wanted.
Heat until hot.

title: chocolate chip rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Brown meat and drain.
Layer in casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste. Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: jamaican jerk chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Marinade chicken in the above for at least one hour.
Cook in wok.

title: linda's cole slaw
directions: Clean
vegetables and shred in food processor or on hand shredder.
Add
salt and pepper to taste.
Add cole slaw dressing and mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: apple pie - "even your husband could make"
directions: Crust Note:
You will also need waxed paper and a rolling pin. Don't scrimp on the flour used on waxed paper to coat side and avoid dough sticking, and on your hands and fingers while handling dough.

title: yummy cream puffs
directions: Dip marshmallows in melted butter & roll in cinnamon sugar. Wrap marshmallow in crescent roll and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 10-12 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Mix together melted margarine and egg.
Add flour and sugar. Combine yeast with warm water and stir into flour mixture.
Let rise 3 hours.
Roll thin.
Put pepperoni and mozzarella cheese in and roll.
Bake at 375 until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, milk, baking powder, flour, egg, pudding mix and juice from peaches.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into buttered oblong pan.
Place drained peaches on top.
Whip softened cream cheese and sugar together.
Spoon on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice burritos
directions: In a skillet, saute onions and garlic in butter until tender. Stir in chicken, chili powder, 1/4 cup broth and 3/4 cup of picante sauce. Heat through; set aside.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In pan, mix all ingredients except egg whites and brown sugar. Stir over low heat until boils.
Chill until set, beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in brown sugar, beat until stiff.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill 4 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line 11 x 13-inch pan with croutons.
Add cheese.
Saute sausage and put on top of cheese.
Beat eggs; add dry mustard, milk, mushroom soup and mushrooms. Pour over croutons, cheese and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: eggplant balls
directions: Cook and drain escarole (save a little water).
Saute several cloves of garlic and remove from oil*.
Add penales, capers, red hot seed and a few fillets of anchovies to oil*.
When penales become tan and anchovies dissolve, throw over escarole.
(If needed, add saved water.)
Serve hot with Italian bread.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Cream together oleo and sugar in large bowl until blended and smooth. Beat in vanilla and egg until light.
Blend baking soda, salt and flour.
Add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Stir in 3/4 cup each of semi-sweet chocolate chips and white chocolate chips and the nuts.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until center tests done (do not overbake).

title: hot dip
directions: Saute onion and
mushrooms in butter.
Combine soup and melt cheese, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli to mixture and stir. Serve hot with nacho chips or etc.

title: apple cider
directions: Tie spices in a cloth.
Mix all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: hawaiian cake(serves 15 to 18)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or regular square pan.

title: lemon fish fillet
directions: Place fish on cookie tray.
Mix ingredients in small bowl; spoon over fish.
Place in refrigerator to marinate 1 to 2 hours. Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until fish flakes.
Serves 4.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and melt. When mixture comes to a complete boil, time it for 3 minutes exactly. Cook for 5 minutes. Add vanilla. Beat until thick. Add some nuts, if you like, and pour into buttered pan.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, vanilla, whipping cream, brandy and milk.
Whip and let set overnight.
Whip egg whites and fold in.
Makes 25 cups.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and dissolve gelatine in a little cold water, then mix together.
Add almost thawed strawberries, pineapple and juice.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of glass dish; refrigerate until firm.
Pour sour cream on top and then the other 1/2 of mixture.
Refrigerate again until firm.

title: yummy pound cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together, then add coconut.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cover chicken pieces with water; salt and pepper to taste. Boil about 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken and debone. Save broth.
Bake large skillet of cornbread.
Crumble cornbread and hamburger bun.
Add chopped onion, sage, pepper, eggs and broth; mix.
Put chicken pieces in bottom of baking dish and pour dressing mixture over it.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: monkey cake
directions: Combine a cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a container with a tight-fitting lid.
Melt butter, remaining 1 cup sugar and remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon to make syrup.
Open 2 cans of biscuits and cut each biscuit into quarters.

Shake biscuit quarters in container to coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place coated biscuit pieces in bottom of greased tube pan; pour 1/2 the syrup over and sprinkle 1/2 the nuts and 1/2 the raisins over syrup.
Cut remaining 2 cans of biscuits into quarters and shake into container to coat with sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange in tube pan over previous layers; add remaining syrup; sprinkle with remaining nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from pan at once and cool on wire rack.
Yields 12 servings.

title: applesauce banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan with vegetable cooking spray and set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.
In a larger bowl mix applesauce, sugar, egg whites, mashed banana and vanilla. Add flour mixture all at once and stir gently, just to blend.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.
Cook uncovered in 375° oven, brushing occasionally with reserved marinade for 30 minutes.
Turn, brush again with marinade, cook until done.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and add ingredients.
Put in mold and let set.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place in baking dish. Cover with Ritz crackers and pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried okra and irish potatoes
directions: Mix okra, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Toss in dry self-rising flour.
Get oil hot, drop vegetables into the hot oil.
Turn often to brown.
Enjoy.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda,
baking
powder,
salt
and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture. Add apples and cinnamon.
Mix together.
Batter will barely cover apples.
Pour
into
greased
x
13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash after cooking.
Chop onion, celery and bell pepper.
Beat eggs.
Mix all together and bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pasta fagiole
directions: In large saucepan or soup pot, coat bottom with olive oil. Chop garlic clove and add to olive oil.
Simmer slowly until oil is very hot.
Add can of cannellini beans, then broth and sauce. Put in one celery stalk and let cook on medium heat until it comes to a boil, then add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir frequently.
Lower heat for remainder of cooking time (approximately 20 minutes).
In separate pot, boil water, add ditalini and cook until soft.
Drain pasta, put into bowls and pour sauce over.
Top with grated cheese and enjoy!

title: ranch seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix seasonings and oil together.
Place oyster crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour seasoning and oil mixture over all crackers. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Spread in cold-cuts keeper container.
Layer pineapple over graham cracker mixture.
Mix 2 cups powdered sugar, cream cheese and egg together until smooth.
Pour over pineapple.
Place 4 to 5 bananas sliced long ways on top.
Cover with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries. Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: boiled fish a la creole
directions: Add salt, lime, thyme, parsley, hot pepper to the boiling water.
Allow to boil rapidly before adding fish. Cook for 20 minutes.
Remove from water.
Serve with drawn butter and lime juice.
Excellent with fungi and vegetables.

title: microwave candy
directions: Combine in 2-quart bowl and microwave for 2 minutes.
Spread in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: homestyle baked beans
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Saute onions and garlic over low heat until tender.
Add beef.
Cook until meat is browned. Drain off excess fat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Transfer to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish or bean pot.
Bake about 45 minutes (in preheated oven at 350°) or until hot and bubbly.
Add salt and pepper.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown onion, garlic, meat and salt in greased skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except 1 can tomato sauce.
Place in casserole.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Wash celery stalks; cut into 3-inch lengths.
Fill with Philadelphia cream cheese or mixture of Blue cheese and sour cream or horseradish and sour cream.
Sprinkle with paprika; garnish with parsley.

title: red punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 quart boiling water and let cool.
Add other ingredients except ginger ale which is added just before serving.
Mix well.
Makes 64 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook, peeled and sliced carrots in salt water until tender, not overcooked.
Drain and cool.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Let stand at least 12 hours.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix together well. Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Check with toothpick.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: In a small bowl, melt margarine in microwave oven.
Add the peanut butter.
Stir well.
Add flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Spread evenly into a square pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 12 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a cup, dissolve baking soda in the buttermilk. In a bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Mix in molasses. Stir spices and salt into flour. Add some of flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk until all ingredients are mixed. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in kettle.
As soon as a batch begins to boil, put in peanuts which have been blanched and let boil, stirring constantly, to hard crack.
Remove from stove. Stir in butter and cut in small pieces.
Salt and return to stove and let boil a minute or so.
Remove from stove.
Add soda.
Pour on buttered pan.

title: judy's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Then place in a casserole pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to an hour.
When done, spread thin layer of catsup on top.
Place back in oven and slightly brown on broil.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Bake at 325°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs.
Measure and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with Hershey's syrup.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: brandy snaps(yields 10 dozen cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Sift flour, sugar and ginger together twice.
Boil the molasses
in a deep saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in melted butter.
While stirring, add the sifted ingredients and mix to a smooth batter.
Drop from a tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet, spacing at least 3-inches apart. Bake at 275° for approximately 15 minutes or until edges start to brown.
Remove from oven and pan immediately and roll each cookie around handle of large wooden spoon or broom handle until cookie is shaped like a cigarette.
Cool shaped cookies on wire rack. Combine whipped cream, brandy and grated sweet chocolate and fill the cooled cookies.
Store in a tightly closed container in refrigerator or freeze until needed.
Remove from freezer approximately 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn dogs
directions: Cover wieners with water.
Add 1/4 cup vinegar.
Boil, drain and cool.
Dip in batter and fry in deep fat, turning until brown. Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with catsup and onions.
Makes 10 or 12 pups.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs and sugars together until light.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Stir in cream and half and half.

title: catalina dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Chop onions, carrots and pepper finely and add to hamburger meat.
Add bread or cracker crumbs to hold together.
Fashion into small balls.
Brown in oil.

title: claudine's banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients except nuts until blended.
Add mashed bananas and beat 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes in angel food pan or 2 loaf pans.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Stir water and gelatin; let dissolve.
Heat pineapple, lemon juice and sugar.
Mix gelatin and pineapple mixture and place in refrigerator until mixture begins to congeal.
Stir grated cheese into mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serve with dressing.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Garnish with stripes of cheese on top.
Bake until hot and bubbly.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple with cherry filling.
Grease well a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and pour fruit mixture into dish.
Over this, crumble dry cake mix.
Slice oleo and sprinkle this over dry cake mix. Sprinkle pecans over this; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Grate cheese until finely grated.
Chop or crush pimentos into very small pieces.
Mix together with mayonnaise until creamy enough to spread or dip.

title: turtle cake
directions: In a bowl, cut margarine in cake mix with fork.
Add water, oil, eggs and 1/2 can of condensed milk.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Melt caramels and 1/2 condensed milk in double boiler.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Spread on hot half of cake.
Add remaining 1/2 of cake batter and bake for 30 minutes.
Make icing.

title: hearty stuffed peppers with tomato sauce
directions: Don't feel like going to McDonald's?
Try this one.
The kids love it and it has much less fat than "Micky D's"!

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: spicy texas chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, bouillon, broth, tomato sauce, pepper juice and water.
Cook over low heat for about 2 hours.
Add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and white pepper.
Cook an additional 30 minutes.
Add salt.
Add flour and water for thickening.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together the margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir in the chocolate bits and nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into 36 bars.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel and grate cucumber (not seeds).
Drain off liquid. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Process in blender until smooth.
Chill and serve with favorite chips.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: roasted salted pecans
directions: Mix with egg white.
Add 1 quart pecan halves.
Cover nuts well.
Pour on foiled-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Stir lemon juice into melted margarine.
(Add more lemon juice if you like a more tangy flavor.)
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Remove from the stove.
(It is not necessary to cook the sauce.)

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Place rind in salt for 3 days.
Remove from brine and let stand in fresh water for 24 hours.
At the end of this time, drop in scalding hot alum water for a few minutes, then in cold water and wipe dry.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Cook until thickens. Remove from stove and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into a cooked pie shell.

title: peachy lemon shake
directions: Place peaches, including the juice, in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth (about 10 seconds).
Blend in milk.
Add sherbet, mixing just until blended.
Pour into glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: choco-mint pound cake
directions: Place 1 or 2 small chocolate mint patties on sliced pound cake.
Heat in toaster oven until melted.
Serve immediately.

title: pizza-burger loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 10-inch skillet, combine first 9 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes, stirring often. Cool 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare hot-roll mix as label directs for pizza dough.
On lightly floured surface, using floured rolling pin, roll dough into a 12-inch square; place on a greased cookie sheet.
Spoon meat mixture down center third of dough to within 2-inches of both ends.
Shape meat into loaf; sprinkle loaf with cheese.
Cut 6 diagonal strips of dough (each 2 inches wide) on each side of meat.
Fold dough ends over meat; then crisscross strips over top.
Brush top of dough with beaten egg; sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
To serve, cut into diagonal slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles as directed; pour over tuna which is in colander. Then place in casserole (that has been buttered) by layers:
tuna, add noodles, eggs and olives and mushroom soup.
Top with eggs, olives, then soup.
Bake in oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Finish at 300° until 45 minutes are up. If more is needed, double the recipe and time.

title: fudge walnut brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, oleo and vanilla. Mix together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to oleo mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake 30 minutes or until set at 350°.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Garnish with whipping cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of water, then add all other ingredients in gallon container and fill container with water. Shake several times the first 4 or 5 hours.

title: grilled marinated potatoes
directions: 1. Slice the potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick pieces. Using the tip of a sharp knife make cross hatch slashes 1/4-inch deep and 1/4-inch apart in the flesh of each potato half without cutting into the skin.
