This should look like a grid pattern. 2. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place potatoes in glass casserole dishes.
Pour marinade over potatoes evenly. 3. Cover each dish with plastic wrap and microwave seperately 10 minutes turning potatoes once 1/2 way through. 4. Place potatoes on a preheated grill.
Cover and cook until tender (about 20 minutes) turning once 1/2 way through.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Dissolve 2 small packages raspberry jello in 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Pour in 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch dish.
Add crushed pineapple, drained, and sliced bananas.
Let set.
Spread sour cream on top.
Let set until cold.
Dissolve 2 packages raspberry jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add thawed package of raspberries.
Chill until cold and then spoon onto top of sour cream.
Let set.
This is good enough to be a dessert!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon out on greased cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over very low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Stir in flour, vanilla, salt and nuts; pour into pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into pieces.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and set aside to cool. Beat eggs.
Mix in sour cream and stir in cooled butter.
Add corn and cornbread mix.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: sweet potato fluff souffle
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot and green pepper; let stand 1 hour.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Note:
These recipe ingredients should all be put together the night before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except for apples.
Fold in the apples (this mixture will be extra thick).
Nuts may be added. Bake 1 hour at 325° or until you think it is done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese stand until room temperature (soft). Mix well; roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour on a Pam greased cookie sheet.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Add onions, salt and pepper, along with the soup.
Layer alternately with cooked egg noodles and grated cheese in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and top with Chinese noodles and almonds.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: louisiana spanish rice
directions: Mix well. Pour into a quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 400° to 450°.
Stir occasionally.

title: oklahoma cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, flour, nuts, baking soda, vanilla and pineapple with a spoon.
Do not use a mixer.
Spray or grease bottom only of a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour in batter and bake for 40-45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat Crisco in medium skillet on medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir-fry until soft, but not browned.
Remove from heat. Cool slightly.
Stir in catsup, lemon juice, honey, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, hot pepper sauce, salt and liquid smoke, if used.
Stir until well blended.
Use over your favorite meat.

title: western pot roast
directions: In heavy pot, brown on all sides the beef brisket or boneless round or chuck roast in oil.
Add chopped onion.
Cook until golden. Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, cider vinegar and salt.
Pour over meat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Serve, sliced, with sauce along with onions, carrots and potatoes, if desired.

title: chili spaghetti
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and crisp.
Pour off most of the grease.
Chop 1 medium-size onion.
Crush 1 pod garlic.
Cook until onion is tender.
Remove from skillet.
Open tomato paste and heat to remove any excess liquid.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer slowly; add chili powder, salt and pepper (cayenne) to taste. Simmer slowly at least 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
This is good with plain lettuce salad and French bread (garlic butter).

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook the rhubarb, sugar and 1/4 cup water together for 5 minutes; set aside and cool.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water; let cool.
Fold rhubarb mixture, banana and cubed cream cheese into slightly thickened gelatin.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: special oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in eggs and vanilla or lemon flavor.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and pecans. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef-rice casserole
directions: Brown beef until crumbly.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Before serving, add 1 cup either grated or crumbled Velveeta cheese. Delish!

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container in a dry place.
Use 1/3 cup in 8 ounces of hot water or heaping teaspoonful to taste.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn warm in a 275° oven. Combine corn syrup, sugar and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Cook without stirring for 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and food coloring; mix well. Pour syrup slowly over popped corn in a fine stream, mixing with a wooden spoon. When cool enough to handle, but still quite warm, shape into 2 to 2 1/2-inch balls. Don't pack too tightly. Makes 12 to 18 popcorn balls.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from bell peppers.
In large skillet, bring water to a boil.
Cook peppers for 5 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Cook rice according to package directions.
In a skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, herbs, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.

title: southern baked beans
directions: place beans in cooking dish and add other ingredients.
Top with cooked bacon.
Cook 45 minutes at 375° salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Freeze 1 quart of cherry soda for beverage cubes.
Chill remaining soft drinks.
When ready to serve, shave or crack beverage cubes; place in a punch bowl.
Add other soft drinks slowly.
Garnish with orange or lemon slices.
Makes 24 servings.

title: gumpke
directions: Remove cores of cabbages.
Boil whole heads and drain.
Set aside.
Brown meat mixture; season to taste.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Use the tweezers to remove the prepared fortunes from the cookies.
Use the opposite end of the tweezers to push your own fortunes into the cookies.
Personalizing your own cookies can be lots more fun than the prepared ones.

title: biscuit tortoni(biscotta di tortoni)
directions: Place
paper
liners
in regular size muffin tins.
Mix crushed macaroons, crushed almonds, sugar and 1 cup cream (not whipped);
blend
well.
Whip
remaining
cream
and fold into macaroon mixture with liqueur and rum.
Spoon into muffin cups and freeze at least 2 hours.
Top with whole almonds.

title: baked scallops(old recipe from boston herald)
directions: Lay scallops in casserole.
Mix sherry and canned soup.
Add shrimp.
Pour soup and sherry over all.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Blend crumbs and butter.
Spread over all and bake 15 minutes plus.
Test doneness of scallops.

title: orange and almond salad
directions: *I use Giant brand old fashioned French with 1/2 olive oil and 1/2 vegetable or canola oil and a large tablespoon of some good kind of mustard, such as Grey Poupon or Dijon.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Boil chicken and drain.
Layer chicken in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat all ingredients adding each individually.
Bake in lightly greased pan or loaf pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Freezes great in Ziploc bags after wrapping first in foil.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Then soften cream cheese and cream with 2 cups powdered sugar.
Mix with large Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust. Pour blueberry pie filling over the top.
Chill well.

title: mom's cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Add flour and milk; beat again.
Grease tube pan well and flour.
Put cake into oven while it is cold.
Turn oven to 300° and bake for 1 hour.
Turn oven up to 325°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients (do not heat).
Makes enough dressing for 1 medium head of cabbage, grated coarsely or sliced finely.
Slaw will be nice for several days by being kept in refrigerator.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook venison and onions over medium heat in a little oil in a large pot until brown, stirring frequently.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat; simmer at least 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Blend onion-mushroom mix with 1/2 cup water.
Combine ground beef, corn, bread crumbs and 6 tablespoons of onion-mushroom mixture.
Mix well.

title: pineapple-glazed spareribs
directions: In large roasting pan, mix soy sauce, sherry, ginger, onions and garlic clove.
Place spareribs in soy sauce mixture, turning each portion to coat well.
Arrange spareribs meat side down in roasting pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
With pastry brush, baste ribs with soy sauce mixture in pan, occasionally.
Turn ribs over and bake 20 minutes.
In measuring cup, drain 1/4 cup juice from pineapple; stir in brown sugar.
Brush ribs with brown sugar mixture.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until ribs are fork tender. Spoon pineapple over ribs; bake 10 minutes or until pineapple is hot.

title: florida salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in a large salad bowl.
Drizzle avocados with with lemon juice.
Arrange avocados, shrimp, cheese, tomatoes and cucumber on lettuce.
Mix together cocktail sauce and mayonnaise. Serve with salad.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: black joe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Simmer the hambone and soaked beans in 3 qts. water for 2 hours.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour longer. Remove hambone: chop pieces of meat and return to soup.
Mash beans if needed to thicken soup.

title: irish hot chocolate
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan blending in water. Bring heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir and boil 2 minutes. Add milk and heat (not to boil).
Pour 1 tablespoon whiskey in each 6-ounce cup.
Add hot cocoa and top with whipped cream.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix tomatoes, soups, broth, onion and spices.
Cook together about 10 minutes.
Add chicken in bite size pieces.
In large 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer Doritos, cheese and chicken mix.
Repeat and cook at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch 1
directions: Mix berries and pineapple in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle sugar. Add cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts.
Pour melted margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Wash salmon and place on foil lined pan.
Place small pieces of shaved butter or margarine, approximately one piece per square inch, on one side of salmon.
Cut very thin slices of onion and place on top of the butter or margarine.
Pour enough lemon juice on steaks to coat all surfaces (a small amount may be used by tilting pan and spooning over steaks).
Leave juice in pan. Seasoning may be added, if desired.
Cook under preheated oven broiler for 7 to 10 minutes per side, depending on broiler temperature.
Do not overcook.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in bowl, stir well.
Add cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Serve chilled.

title: spicy oriental caramelized beef
directions: In large shallow glass baking dish, blend sugar, soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic powder and pepper; add beef and turn to coat. In a large skillet, heat 1/2 inch oil to 350°. Fry beef in three batches until brown and crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon; drain on paper towels. Garnish, if desired, with sliced green onions and crushed red pepper.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large pot, heat water and crumbled bouillon cubes.
When boiling, add macaroni.
Cook according to package instructions until tender.
Drain well.
Cut ham into small strips.
Place a layer of pasta over bottom of a lightly greased pan.
Sprinkle with some ham.
Repeat last step.
In a bowl, whisk together eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over macaroni.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: cheese pies(ftoier ghibaen)
directions: Let dough rise.
Shape dough into 8 balls and place of a cloth about 4 inches apart.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Combine all the filling ingredients in a mixing bowl and
with beater until smooth and well blended.
Roll out balls of dough and make into circles.
Divide filling equally on all circles and close. To close, bring two edges of circle toward center and seal by pressing dough together between finger tips.
Bring bottom up to make a triangle and seal.
Bake on lightly oiled cookie sheet at 400°
until golden brown, about 5-10 mins.

title: broccoli dip
directions: *If Kraft garlic cheese is unavailable, substitute Velveeta and season with garlic salt to taste.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mix, then place in a 2-quart casserole. Dot top with 4 tablespoons butter. Cover with foil. Press down on entire top of the potatoes. Refrigerate (will keep a week). Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili, cheese and chips
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder and onion.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Place chips on 5 plates.
Pour beef mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 5.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add Velveeta and stir over low heat until
melted.
Add seasonings.
Spread on rye bread and place on cookie sheets.
Freeze.
When frozen, place in plastic bags and freeze until ready to bake.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: stir-fried shrimp appetizers
directions: Combine soy sauce, wine, green onions, garlic and ginger.
Stir in shrimp and let stand 12 minutes.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Drain shrimp and add to pan.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Serve immediately.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix together all of ingredients.
Top with crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry-raspberry salad
directions: Thaw and drain raspberries; measure liquid from berries and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat liquid and dissolve jello. Fold cranberry sauce into jello mixture with mixer.
Then fold in sour cream with mixer until sour cream dissolves.
Stir in raspberries.
Refrigerate until firm.
Goes well with poultry and ham dinners.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown
ground
beef; drain.
Add 1 can enchilada sauce. Fry tortillas
one
at a time in oil until soft.
Lay on paper towel to	drain.	Put
about
tablespoon meat in center of tortilla. Add
small	amount of cheese.
Roll up and put seam side down in dish.
When all of them are rolled up, cover with remaining meat. Pour some ketchup over the meat.
Pour on the 2
cans
of sauce. Top with cheese.
Cover with Reynolds wrap and heat for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking and stirring until soft ball stage (234°) or until a small amount forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and as much peanut butter as you wish.
Cool for a few minutes.
Beat until fudge loses its gloss. Pour into buttered pan and finish cooling.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen squares.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for cheese and potato chips.
Put in a casserole dish.
Put cheese and potato chips on top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: combo-fruit pie
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple; add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add sugar and cornstarch to water/juice mixture and cook until thick, stirring.
Fold in fruit, nuts and almond extract.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells and top with whipped topping.

title: perfect challah
directions: Combine yeast with water and sugar in a large bowl and after 5 minutes add 1 cup flour, stirring well.
Cover and let rest for 20 minutes.
Now add salt, oil and eggs less the one yolk which you will use to glaze the loaf.
Stir in last of flour and knead on a board for 5 minutes.
Grease and seal into refrigerator to rise slowly overnight.
Divide dough in two the next morning then each half into three ropes of dough.
Braid three ropes and tuck in ends and place on a greased baking sheet.
Let rise to double and glaze with a mixture of the egg yolk with 1 teaspoon water and a pinch of salt.
Sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 15 minutes.
I make this at Easter.

title: chili
directions: Put everything in one big pot.
Cook for about 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Put 2 large heads of dill in each quart jar.
Fill with pickles lengthwise.
Put garlic bulbs on top.
Heat water, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Cold pack about 5 minutes.
Then remove right away.
Let set several weeks before using.

title: minute steaks
directions: Coat steaks with flour.
Melt shortening in skillet.
Cook steaks over medium-high heat until brown and crispy, about 4 minutes on each side.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and soften cream cheese. Mix cake mix, egg, margarine and cream cheese together.
Add your choice of chocolate chips, etc.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 1 hour.

title: babom's 2-quart zucchini casserole
directions: Slice and boil zucchini and onion for 5 minutes.
Brown sausage in pan.
Add Stove Top chicken stuffing.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots. Add to zucchini mixture.
Put layer of sausage on bottom of dish and then layer stuffing, then zucchini mixture, another layer of sausage mixture and top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Combine all.
Marinate seafood, chicken, pork or beef in sauce. Baste meat in pan or on grill.
The sauce will keep in covered jar for 1 week.

title: tuna in pita pocket
directions: Combine tuna, celery, onion and cheese spread; stir well. Layer lettuce, cucumber and tuna mixture in pita halves.
Top each with tomato.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Make honey mustard sauce ahead of time.
Keep refrigerated. Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine mustard and honey in small bowl. Stir in dill and orange peel.
Line a baking sheet with foil. Place chicken skin side down.
Brush on sauce.
Pull back skin on chicken and brush with sauce.
Bake until juices run clear (about 30 minutes).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs. Stir in milk. Add bananas. Sift well the flour and dry ingredients. Add nuts. Pour into well-greased 9 x 3-inch pan. Let stand 20 minutes before baking. Bake for 1 hour at 325° or 350° until tests done.

title: crack-r-jack
directions: Prepare a brown paper bag by spraying with Pam until well coated.
Place the following in a 4-cup glass bowl:
brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High until it is boiling.
Continue cooking after reaching the boil stage for 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir well (mixture will be foamy).
Place popped corn and peanuts in bag and pour syrup over corn; shake well.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes and shake.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes and shake, then microwave for 3 seconds.
Shake and pour on cookie sheet to cool.

title: celery soup
directions: Cook celery until soft.
Add broth mix.
Pour into blender. Add milk; blend for 10 to 15 seconds.
Reheat and serve.

title: fruit or vegetable dressing
directions: Mix well; set aside for a few days.
The longer, the better. This dressing gets thicker and thicker.
Good on fruit salad, cabbage slaw, raisin salad and head lettuce.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Heat chocolate with milk to melting.
Beat egg yolks and beat into chocolate; cool.
Beat egg whites and fold into chocolate. Beat whipping cream and sugar.
Add to mixture.
Break cake into small chunks and mix into chocolate.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with nuts.
Refrigerate.
(Can be frozen.)

title: frozen raspberry salad
directions: In top of a double boiler, combine marshmallows and orange juice. Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently, until marshmallows are melted.
Let cool.

title: cheese straws
directions: Soften butter and cheese.
Mix together with clean hands. Put dough in cookie press using cheese straw disc, bake on cookie sheet at 350 degrees until done (lightly browned).

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate potatoes.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and add sugar, nutmeg, vanilla, salt and milk.
Melt butter in casserole dish to coat. Pour excess butter into mixture.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for a little over an hour.
Remove cover for about the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Cook on cookie sheet at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Take out and put into sauce.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add dry taco mix and refried beans.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make the cheese sauce and pour over beans and beef mixture.
Add the grated cheese on top.
Mix sour cream and taco sauce together and layer it on top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with all the optional ingredients if desired.
Serve with taco chips.

title: coconut pie(with its own crust)
directions: Stir together flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat all together until well mixed.
Put in buttered pie plate (10-inch).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: red waldorf cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Mix cocoa and food coloring and add to above.
Sift salt and flour and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Mix baking soda and vinegar and add last.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: marshmallow cake(makes 35 pieces)
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add boiling water and mix.
Cool.
Beat egg whites, salt and baking powder until stiff; add vanilla.
Fold into cooled batter.
Bake in greased and floured 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and salsa.
Spread on tortillas. Put a thin slice of beef on top.
Roll up tortillas and cut into 1-inch slices and hold with a toothpick.
Chill.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand 10 minutes.
Blend remaining ingredients and mix with the liquid mixture.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead down and let rise a second time. Shape into rolls; cover with a cloth and let stand overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Bake next morning at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.
Yields 36 rolls.

title: beef patties with onions
directions: Saute onions in oleo until golden.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook until onions are tender.
Remove and set aside.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, water, mustard, salt and pepper.
Form into patties.
Brown patties on both sides.
Drain.
Add water and onions; simmer until patties are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot cake
directions: Put all ingredients of cake in bowl and beat 4 minutes at high speed.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers, take seeds out and fill with the remaining ingredients mixed together.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: russian mousse
directions: Mix sugar, gelatine and water.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Add almond extract.
Pour mixture into sour cream and mix.
Chill until congealed.
Blend in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into mold; chill until set.

title: baked barley
directions: Saute the barley in the butter or margarine until barley kernels are lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Put in casserole with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, adding more water as needed.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add broccoli, onion and celery. Saute until onion and celery are clear, about 10 minutes.
Add soup and rice.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese melts, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Beat all ingredients 2 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven in layer pans or loaf pans.
Frost with a favorite topping.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Pat firmly in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over very low heat. Pour over peanut butter mixture.
Cut when cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Cream instant pudding,	pineapple
juice and Cool Whip. Add crushed pineapple and
nuts and fold in marshmallows.
Mix well. Chill until ready to serve.

title: fried frog logs
directions: Salt and pepper frog legs.
Dip legs into egg mixture and batter in cracker crumbs.
Drop legs in hot oil and brown on both sides.
Don't overcook.
Guaranteed to make you tap your foot when eating.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Bake at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs,	one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour
and
soda;
add
to
creamed mixture alternately with sour
cream.
Mix	well
after each addition. Stir
in flavoring.
Pour
batter
into
greased
and
floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at	350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove
from pan and cool completely.	Yield: one 10-inch cake.

title: cabbage scallop
directions: Boil chopped cabbage until tender.
Drain.
Heat 2 cups of stewed tomatoes.
Add the tomatoes to a mixture of :
flour, sugar, margarine, onions and pepper.
In a greased casserole, alternate layers of cabbage and tomatoes mix.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: vegetarian tater tots casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of an oblong casserole dish with Tater Tots. Spread onion over Tater Tots.
Add butter to top of onion.
Mix soup and evaporated milk.
Pour over the dish.
Sprinkle cheese over the top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: *May use half and half combination of wheat, white, etc.

title: hello dolly cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in graham crackers and sugar.
Press down and sprinkle coconut on top of crust, then sprinkle chocolate chips and butterscotch chips on top of coconut. Then, pour nuts on.
Pour milk over top of nuts and bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered with foil.
Remove foil; bake 10 more minutes uncovered.

title: t. v. dinner
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Remove mushroom stems and cut up. Combine with mushroom soup and water; set aside.
For each serving, cut a 40-inch length of aluminum foil and fold in half. Arrange meat, potatoes, carrots, onion, green pepper slices and mushrooms in center of foil. .
Spoon the mushroom soup mixture over all.
Top with a tablespoon of margarine.
Double fold top and edges to seal securely.
Place in center of grill and cook for 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve in foil.
May be cooked in conventional oven at 350°, but the flavor is better if cooked on the grill outside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken into bite-size pieces.
In large bowl put mushroom soup, milk and cheese.
Add chicken, macaroni and boiled eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss bread crumbs with remaining 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: chocolate trifle(teacher favorite)
directions: You will also need 1 glass bowl or trifle dish.

title: frosting for brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, boil milk, margarine and sugar for 1 minute.
Add chips and stir until smooth.
Place pan in cold water and stir until proper consistency.	Will frost 9 x 13 pan of brownies.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill for two hours or longer. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
I usually double this recipe.

title: violet's cheesecake
directions: Grease spring-form pan bottom and sides; melt butter.
Mash down Social Tea Biscuits until very fine; pour in melted butter and mix.
Spread on bottom of spring-form pan to form crust.
Separate the egg yolks from the egg whites in two separate bowls.
First beat egg whites with electric mixer until very stiff in one bowl. In a separate bowl, put together egg yolks, the cream cheese, sugar and the vanilla.
Beat ingredients in with electric mixer until creamy smooth.
Now you pour your stiff egg whites into your mixture and fold them in mixture by hand or on low with electric mixer.
Pour entire mixture into spring-form pan.
Bake in oven approximately 50 minutes to an hour (or when toothpick inserted comes out clean) at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill 24 hours ahead.
Use on fresh vegetables, etc.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple (I like the oranges whole) and mix together.
Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese and gently stir in dry jello until blended.
Then mix both mixes together and chill.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or two smaller ones.
This makes a big congealed salad.
If you like orange taste you'll love it.
Can be cut in half for 1 or 2 people.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold into Dream Whip.
Break cake into bite size pieces and fold into Dream Whip mixture.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread prepared cherry pie filling over all and chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add lemon juice, cream cheese, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk. Beat with mixer until smooth. Add fruit, marshmallows and nuts. Chill in fridge several hours or overnight.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix with potatoes.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake another 20 minutes at 400°.

title: lo-cal cukes
directions: Mix first three ingredients in shaker.
Pour over cuke slices. Cover tight.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine butter, Crisco, cream of tartar, salt, eggs, sugar, soda and flour.
Press into a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes; cool.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press crescent roll out flat, 1 can per pan if the pan is fairly small.
Bake until golden brown on top.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, blend butter, sugar, eggs, chocolate syrup, sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour, chocolate chips, baking powder and salt.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: sweet rice
directions: In a saucepan, put in rice, water and salt.
Cook until tender.
Add milk.
Cook on low heat.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add more milk if it thickens too much. It will thicken more when cooled. Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Serves 4.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add beaten egg and mix.
Add vinegar and water and stir well.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly or in double boiler until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter. Stir until melted.
Cool and add salad dressing or mayonnaise. Keeps in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: tuscan chicken and pasta
directions: Mix equal amounts of bread crumbs and cheese (enough to dredge chicken breasts).
Mix egg whites with a few drops of water and pinch of salt.
Dip chicken breasts in egg whites and then dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Saute in olive oil until browned on outside, but not cooked through. Remove and keep warm. Add more oil, if needed, to saute onions until soft.
Add sun-dried tomatoes with their oil, mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Stir and toss until mushrooms wilt.
Add chicken broth, basil, olives and zest and return chicken to pot. Simmer, covered, until chicken is cooked through and sauce is hot. Serve over angel hair pasta and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Blend together flour, nuts and butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix together the chocolate and vanilla pudding with the milk and spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and shaved chocolate.

title: sweet apple pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, sour cream and flavorings.
Mix well. Pour into crusts.
Run a knife through apples while still in can to cut into smaller pieces.
Arrange apples over pies.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: baker's icing
directions: Boil the milk and sugar about 10 minutes. When cold, add to the Crisco and vanilla. Beat well.

title: banana nut crumble
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually with vanilla.
Fold in crumbs and nuts.
Grease a 7 x 11-inch pan with oleo.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Slice about 4 bananas over the top, then add the Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with raw vegetables.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Over low heat melt butter, brown sugar and pancake syrup. Blend well and add nuts.

title: kumquat relish
directions: Wash, chop or slice fruit; removing seeds.
Put fruit into water.
Add spice and sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bring mixture to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts and liqueur.

title: english peas with cheese sauce
directions: Melt cheeses and mix with mushroom soup.
Add peas and heat thoroughly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter until soft and add sugar, beaten eggs, cornstarch and vanilla.
Beat until blended well. Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown and set firm.

title: soft tortilla roll-ups
directions: Add green chilies to softened cream cheese.
Mix in garlic powder and chili powder.
Spread thin on tortillas.
Roll tightly. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Serve with picante sauce, 16 ounce jar, mild.

title: golden green pepper bake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Remove seeds and parboil peppers 5 minutes. Combine canned or frozen corn, tomatoes and cheese.
Spoon into peppers.
Top with bread crumbs that have been tossed in melted butter.
Bake in baking dish 30 to 35 minutes.

title: herman
directions: Mix together in plastic or glass container and let stand overnight in a warm place with a lid, but do not cover tightly. Refrigerate, covered, but stir each day.
On the fifth day, feed with 1 cup flour, 1 cup milk and 1/2 cup sugar.
You can use this starter to make the Amish Friendship Bread.

title: easy chess pie variation
directions: Beat eggs; melt oleo.
Mix all ingredients together using a whisk.
Bake at 275° in an unbaked pie shell until firm.
Takes about 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cinnamon over top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch pan the beef on bottom and then corn.
Dilute soup with water and pour on top of corn.
Place Tater Tots on top of soup mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli casserole(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cut buds from broccoli stems.
Peel stems using a potato peeler and cut stems into 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam stems and buds until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Saute in butter the celery, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and steamed broccoli until all vegetables are tender.
Add the chicken and seasonings.
Add the cream cheese to the mixture and blend over low heat until the cream cheese is melted.
Pour mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Heat in a 350° oven until top is golden brown.

title: texas brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In heavy saucepan, combine oleo, shortening, brewed coffee and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar in bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using wooden spoon or high speed on electric mixer.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until browned.
Drain.
In blender, puree tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, celery, chili powder, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line bottom of cooked pie crust with cream cheese, softened to room temperature. Arrange whole strawberries on top of cream cheese. Put crushed strawberries, sugar and cornstarch in pan and cook until thickened.
Cool and pour over whole berries. Before serving, top with whipped cream.

title: sliced zucchini pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Pour over zucchini and onions; let stand 1 hour.
Bring to a boil again and cook 3 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 quarts.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together cornstarch (or flour), sugar and cocoa.
Add 1/4 cup milk (or enough to make mixture easy to pour).
Set aside.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place lettuce, broken cauliflower, red onion and bacon in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese together and spread over salad.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Stir 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken stir fry
directions: In a skillet spayed with cooking spray, stir fry chicken, half at a time.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Remove skillet from heat, spray with cooking spray.
Stir fry vegetables until crisp-tender.
Add soup, water, soy, ginger and stir-fried chicken.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion until crisp-tender.
Combine cream-style corn and whole kernel corn, eggs, and corn muffin mix; blend well.
Add onion mixture and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until firm and set.
Makes 12 half-cup servings.

title: grandma nelson's pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan; thicken over medium heat, then pour into unbaked pie crust.
Top with another crust. Sprinkle with butter and sugar and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: chicken en croute
directions: Poach the chicken breasts in chicken broth and sherry for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Cool and drain. Split chicken breasts in half lengthwise and wrap each piece in a thin slice of ham; coat it with a thin layer of Dijon style mustard. Sprinkle with tarragon and wrap in cheese. Place thawed puff pastry shells on a lightly floured surface; roll out each into a 4 inch circle. Wrap each chicken breast with a pastry circle. Wet edges with water, crimp and seal. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until puffed and golden. Serves 6.

title: mexican skillet dinner
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add soups and picante sauce. Stir until blended.
Add chili powder and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add tortilla pieces.
Stir.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients, except biscuits.
Bring to boil.
Quarter each biscuit and mix with syrup and nuts.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put half of sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet, one bottle at a time.
Add remaining sherbet.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute all ingredients until shrimp is pink and thoroughly cooked (about 10 minutes).
Squeeze juice of 1 lemon over after cooked.
Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni in 3 quarts boiling, salted water for 10 minutes. When cooked, rinse with cold water and drain.
Add remaining ingredients to macaroni.

title: date cookies
directions: Cook condensed milk and dates in double boiler until dark and creamy; stir constantly.
Turn off heat, but leave in boiler; stir in pecans.
Spoon on crackers and bake at 350° for about 6 to 8 minutes or until brown.
Let cool completely.
Mix softened cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy. Top on cooled crackers.

title: banana tea loaf
directions: Beat eggs, margarine, bananas and sugar.
Pour over dry ingredients just to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan glazed pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl beat together eggs, pumpkin, milk, 3/4 cup sugar and spice.
Place frozen crust on preheated baking sheet.
Pour filling into crust.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix 1/2 hour or 45 minutes before serving.
Use the flavor of sherbet for the desired color you want.

title: john's rice
directions: Boil rice and water until water is gone. Saut onion in butter and add mushrooms. Stir in 2 cans of soup and rice. Pour into casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Rice will not be soupy when done.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together like a pie crust.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water and set aside to cool.
Put cake in bowl, add oil and eggs.
Mix well; then add the gelatin and water (cooled).
Bake in either greased tube or 13 x 9 inch pan. If tube pan is used, bake 1 hour at 300 degrees; if 13 x 9 inch pan is used, bake 325 degrees for 35 minutes.
While cake is still warm - spoon the following mixture over it.
Bring to a boil:

title: sensational sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter.
Beat egg, lemon and vanilla into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking soda and gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle on sugar. Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
(If dough seems a little dry, add milk until you reach the right consistency.)

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Put in mixing bowl in order given.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes for bread.
For muffins, fill tins 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 40 muffins.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a lightly greased casserole dish. Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: warm spinach and tomato toss
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook sliced onion and garlic in oil 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Increase heat to high; add baby spinach, cherry tomato halves and salt.
Cook 5 minutes or more or until spinach is tender and tomatoes are juicy, stirring frequently.
Serve salad warm or at room temperature. Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in skillet.
While they brown, mix all remaining ingredients, except the onion rings and sour cream, in a bowl.
Separate onion rings; place on pork chops.
Pour mixture over chops; simmer for 1 1/4 hours.
Add the sour cream; cook for another 15 minutes.
Especially good served over rice.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 375° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Brown in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour a little in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Fill 6 to 8 flour tortillas with generous amount of mixture.
Roll up and place in pan.
Pour remaining mixture over top.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Melt over low heat the peanut butter and butter; add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix and pack in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Melt chocolate chips, butter and marshmallows.
Pour quickly over peanut butter mixture.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine salad dressing, flour, salt and pepper in saucepan. Gradually add milk and cook on low heat, stirring constantly. Add cheese and stir until melted. Place potatoes in baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over potatoes. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peaches amaretto
directions: Combine peaches and Amaretto. Chill 1 hour.
Top with cookies.

title: crab puffs
directions: Melt cheese and butter over low heat.
Add all seasonings; mix well.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise and crab.
Spread on muffins.
Cut into 6 pieces and freeze.
Bake frozen pieces about 10 minutes at 450°.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine in blender until chopped.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Saute veggies in oil until soft (do not burn).
Add a little more oil, if you feel mixture is too dry.
Add cold rice, meat and soy sauce to make rice brown.
Then add beaten egg and freshly ground pepper.
Fry another minute or two.

title: new england slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, horseradish and seasoning.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve in a bowl lined with cabbage leaves, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato berry bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook, peel and slice sweet potatoes in 1/2.
If canned, drain and slice in half.
Place in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, sliced side down.
Top with berries and nuts; dot with marmalade.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix the shortening, flour and salt together until coarse and crumbly.
Add the water and vinegar; mix until forms a ball. Makes four single or two double crust pies.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Combine all in a bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil. Remove from skillet. Add onion, garlic and pepper to remaining oil; saute 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook 5 minutes. Add chicken, bay leaf, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Add rice. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Add peas and pimentos. Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs, oil, instant pudding and vanilla.
Put 1/2 of cake mixture in fluted pan.
Mix cocoa, cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Add half of cinnamon and sugar mixture on layer of cake mixture, then rest of cake mixture.
Top with second half of cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Clean and break cauliflower apart.
Boil until tender.
Strain and cool.
Dip in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil. Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar; add buttermilk and mix well. Add dry ingredients and 100% Bran. Then add soaked All-Bran and raisins. Place in muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes. Bake as many as you like; store remaining batter in a covered jar in refrigerator. Will keep for 1 month.

title: spaghetti
directions: Mix all canned contents together.
Add garlic salt, salt, pepper, lemon flavor, pepper seed, sage and Coke.
Stir together and place on medium heat.
Scramble hamburger meat in frypan until brown.
Mix with sauce.
Cut up bell pepper and onion; smother fry until soft.
Mix with other ingredients and cook on low heat for 4 hours.
Take lid off last hour to cause water to evaporate.
Then it is ready to eat.

title: taco salad
directions: *BLKLIN man, never gets a homemade biscuit; he eats from a cardboard can.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together with other ingredients. Top with saltines and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pickled mangoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil.	Cool; pour over mangoes.
Add Li-Hing Mui.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Grate potatoes in a large bowl.
Stir in sour cream and onions.
Add 1 cup of grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, until heated through, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together meat and rice; saute bacon and onion until brown. Add to meat mixture with egg.
Scald peppers and reserve.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Pour 1 can tomato soup with about 2 cans of water over the pepper in a large pot and cook slowly (cover slightly) for about 1 hour.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In a large bowl, mix sweet peas, pickles, onion and boiled eggs.
Add tuna and macaroni.
Mix well with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Refrigerate (overnight is best).

title: deluxe corn bread
directions: Mix egg with corn and sour cream.
Add muffin mix.
Cook in 9-inch greased square pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° to 400°. Also good sliced, buttered and toasted.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt chocolate slowly over double boiler.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Chill.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli noodles
directions: In saucepan, cook noodles as directed on package.
Add seasoning packets.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Heat through. Stir constantly.

title: garden salad
directions: Sprinkle dry dressing mix over vegetables.
Pour bottled dressing over vegetables.
Mix and marinate at least 8 hours. Keeps well.
Lettuce may be added, if desired, just before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together. Top mixture with stuffing in 9 x 12 pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil together well.
Pour over other ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: super hash browns(hearty side dish)
directions: Saute onion in butter.	In
large
bowl,
combine onion and butter with all
other
ingredients,
except potato chips. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan
or
baking
dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: 6 minute cheesecake
directions: Have crumb crust ready and set oven to 325°.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Put in crumb crust and bake 20 minutes.
Hike oven up to 450°.
Spread a cup of sour cream over top of pie and sprinkle a tablespoon of sugar on that.
Bake it for 5 minutes.
Chill it.

title: mormon muffins
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Combine boiling water and baking soda; let cool.
Pour buttermilk over cereals in large bowl.
In separate bowl, cream oil, sugar, honey, molasses and eggs until blended well.
Add creamed mixture to cereal mixture, then add soda water and mix all well.
Add dry ingredients (flours and oatmeal) and blend thoroughly by hand.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream together molasses, brown sugar and butter.
Stir in all remaining ingredients and let stand several minutes to soften bran flakes.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, watching closely to prevent burning.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges together.
Add sugar to mixture and mix.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add cold water.
Before jello sets firmly, add cranberry mixture.
One-half cup of chopped pecans may be added to mixture.

title: "melt in your mouth" sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given and refrigerate 2 hours.
Take a teaspoon of dough and roll into ball.
Roll in sugar.
Press down with a glass. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or less.
Watch closely.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour in casserole dish, beans and sauce mixture.
Place bacon on top and cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and
debone.
Boil noodles; drain, and set aside. Saute onion and
bell pepper in margarine.
Put onion, pepper, soups, cheese and
tomatoes in boiler on low heat long enough to melt cheese.
Pour	over
noodles and mix.	Place in large casserole dish
and
bake
approximately
minutes at 325°.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water.
In separate bowl, mix flour, powdered milk, cinnamon, allspice and salt.
Add shortening and cut in.
Add yeast mixture, egg and currants.
Beat well, then knead briefly.
Let rise in greased bowl until double in bulk. Punch down; shape into rolls and place in greased pan.
Let double in size, then bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Frost with cross on top with mixture of powdered sugar and water. Makes about 30 large buns.

title: orange nut bread
directions: In large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
In a second bowl, combine last 3 ingredients and mix into first, stirring just until moist.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 2 minutes, no longer.
Add pecans and beat well.
Pour on cake or brownies.

title: royal coconut cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly; drop from spoon onto baking cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat in 1/4-inch diagonal strips and put in a bowl.
Add Kitchen Bouquet and toss until all the meat is well coated.
Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons hot oil in a Dutch oven until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Add remaining oil to that in the Dutch oven and brown beef strips and simmer gently until beef is tender.
Add mushrooms.
Blend cornstarch and mushroom broth.
Add and cook, stirring.
Makes enough for 6 served over rice or noodles.
(Could serve about 25 at a potluck.)

title: key biscayne lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; stir in milk, lime juice, peel and food coloring. Beat 1 egg white until stiff; fold into milk mixture. Turn into pastry shell. Beat reserved egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry. Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown. Cool. Chill before serving.

title: anna's biscuits
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Cut in shortening as for pie crust.
Stir in milk.
Knead slightly on floured cloth.
Cut and bake in a 350 degree oven until golden brown.

title: seafood lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomato sauce.
Spread 1/3 cup of mixture on each noodle.
Roll.
Place in baking pan.
Pour sauce over rolls.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: green salad crunch
directions: Saute almonds and noodles in butter until lightly browned. Allow to cool.
Wash and tear lettuce and add other ingredients.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and gelatin.
Add eggs and oil.
Fold in strawberries.
Bake at 325° in layer pans until cake tests done.

title: pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: 12 bean soup
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Soup broth will look black during first cooking.
Check beans to see if they are tender before adding the rest of the ingredients.
Add all ingredients except ginger.
Simmer another 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add ginger.
Serve with dark bread for a complete protein.

title: popcorn pops
directions: Combine popcorn and peanuts in large bowl or pan.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine molasses, sugar and salt; cook over medium heat to hard ball stage (260°).
Pour syrup slowly over popped corn and nuts, stirring until mixture is well coated.
Press into 5-ounce cold drink cups.
Insert a wooden skewer in each and let cool. Push up bottoms of cup to remove.
Makes 16.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Pound round steak on both sides.
Rub oil on one side.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add bread.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Slice boiled eggs over steak; roll up, tie and brown.
Put in baking pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, or until tender.

title: bachelor stew
directions: Combine rice and water.
Boil rice until most of the water is cooked down.
Add tomato sauce, onion, hamburger meat, butter and salt.
Cook a little longer and cover and let stand off of burner.

title: old-fashioned nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

title: three layer pie
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch baking pan (350° oven).

title: fresh strawerry pie
directions: Bake pie crust by package directions.
Let cool.
Wash and dry strawberries.
Chop mix glaze and strawberries.
Pour in cooled pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in Refrigerator until cool.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until smooth.
Pour in greased 8-inch square pan.	Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes (can mix by hand or in blender).

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and barbecue sauce until sugar is dissolved. Keep in separate bowl. In large pot, place roast, diced onion and tomatoes, smashing tomatoes. Pour sauce over roast; cover and set overnight in refrigerator. Early next morning, heat oven to 250° and cook roast for 12 hours. When done, shred meat with forks. Separate meat from sauce and serve on big rolls.

title: southern-style potatoes
directions: Rinse and drain hash browns.
Set aside.
Combine the butter, garlic, onions and mushrooms in a non-stick pan and saute until the onions are clear.
Drain.

title: cherry nut bars
directions: Combine
flour,
oats,	sugar, pecans, soda and butter. Save 1 1/2 cups of this mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into a
x
13-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes. Gently
spoon filling over crust, then sprinkle with marshmallows. Top
with	reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes more.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut together lard, flour and salt. Add beaten egg into cup of cold water and vinegar.
Mix well and add to flour mixture.
Mix well and roll out.
Makes 3 (10-inch) double crusts.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towel.
Combine butter and salad dressing mix.
With spatula spread mixture over chicken pieces.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place chicken skin side up (not touching) in shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for about an hour or until tender.
No need to turn.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until it looks like coarse cornmeal.
Stir in cheese.	Add milk gradually, using just enough to make a soft dough.
Dough should not be sticky but if it is, just add a little more flour.
Place dough on a floured surface and knead a few times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup and milk mixture over top.
Crumble dressing mixture over top and then hot water and oleo mix.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese, sour cream, onion, garlic, curry, salt and pepper together and chill for several hours before serving. Depending on the size of your serving bowl, you should be able to refill it two or three times during the evening.
Divide the green onion garnish among the servings.

title: beef slices in wine
directions: Cut steak crosswise into diagonal slices, 1/4-inch thick.
In hot Dutch oven, saute slices, a few at a time, until browned. Remove.
Pour off pan drippings.
Add garlic, 1/4 cup parsley, salt, rosemary, basil, oregano, tomato sauce, wine and browned meat.
Simmer, covered and stirring occasionally, until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Add mushrooms and simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer.
Combine 2 tablespoons water and flour.
Mix well. Stir into beef mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute or until thickened.
Cook noodles.
Serve over bed of noodles and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix drained corn, cream of chicken soup and rice together.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a rack. Yield:
One 10-inch cake.

title: italian baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Melt butter in glass baking dish.
Roll potatoes in butter in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle Good Seasons mix on potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done and golden brown.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: jello easter eggs
directions: Measure apple or grape juice into container that can be used on stove top.
Bring juice to a boil.
Add Jello and stir to dissolve.
Boil for 1 - 2 minutes until Jello is well dissolved. Pour into egg mold and place in refrigerator 3 to 6 hours or overnight.
You may swab each egg section with Pam before pouring mixture in.
This makes the eggs come out easier.

title: baked brie and apples
directions: Place Brie in an ovenproof serving dish.
Spread with butter. Arrange almonds over the top.
Bake at 350° until soft and heated through, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm with bread and sliced apples.

title: mom's best meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until well blended.
Put in loaf pan and cover with ketchup.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: fried venison
directions: Soak venison in Italian dressing overnight.
Drain meat; mix flour, salt and pepper.
Cover meat in flour mixture.
Deep fry until brown.
Do not overcook meat.

title: grandma lewis' banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Mix in peanuts and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Thoroughly stir in vanilla and butter and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Mix in baking soda and pour out onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Allow the mixture to cool and then break into pieces.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending each until smooth.
Sift flour, then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: mcvay's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add well beaten eggs. Stir soda in hot water; add to batter.
Add flour and mix.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork into sugar and make crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 60 medium size cookies.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Blend first four ingredients in cooking vessel, bring to a boil.
Add vanilla when mixture comes to soft ball stage.
Cool. Add nuts; beat.

title: tangy broiled halves
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/2 crosswise.
Combine next 5 ingredients and sprinkle evenly over cut tomatoes.
Broil 2 to 3 inches from heat for 3 to 5 minutes until well heated.
Sprinkle parsley over and serve as meat accompaniment.
Serves 4.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger. Spread refried beans in bottom of baking dish. Layer hamburger, taco sauce and grated cheese over the beans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with sour cream.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Add spices to water.
Bring water to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add tea immediately.
Brew 4 minutes; strain.
Add sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit juices.

title: broccoli and pasta
directions: Cook noodles (following package directions); drain. Meanwhile, heat in a large skillet or wok the vegetable oil.
Stir in broccoli, mushrooms and onions.
Stir-fry until the broccoli is crisp-tender (about 4 minutes).
Season lightly with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in cooked noodles and butter until heated through; stir.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Cut in shortening; add water. Flour board and roll the pie crust out thick.
Put in greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: ken's spicy meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, egg, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, garlic, half the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into loaf; place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° while preparing sauce.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water to bowl; mix well.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: lemon daffodil dessert
directions: Combine juice, sugar and condensed milk.
Add whipped cream. Tear cake into small pieces and line bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over cake and mix together lightly. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Place ice cream in a large bowl; cut up and allow to soften. Mix pumpkin, brown sugar, orange juice and spices, using an electric mixer.
Add to the softened ice cream and mix well. Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm. Garnish with whipped cream when served.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake the cake mix as directed on an 11 x 15-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread on cake after it has cooled.
Mix together the drained crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pudding mixture and top with Cool Whip.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.

title: swiss apple dessert
directions: Cook sliced apples in cider, lemon juice and vanilla until mushy.
Let cool.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put in pie shell.
Freeze until solid. Thaw and serve.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Crust:
Heat water and butter until boils.
Remove from heat; add flour.
Stir by hand until it forms a ball.
Let cool.
Stir in unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Spread the mixture over bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch greased glassware pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Check to see if browning.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Oil Pyrex dish.
Mix all together and pour in dish.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for about 30 minutes.
This is not a real firm cornbread.
Can be reheated if placed in foil.

title: zucchini parmesan bake
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and vegetable oil.
Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Cook in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; then add last 3 ingredients.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Rinse broccoli to thaw; drain.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of cheese, the chicken and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth (salt and pepper).
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Work into margarine.
Add flour, cayenne and salt.
Put dough into a cookie press, using the star press.
Place on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken divan
directions: If using leftover meat, cut from bones but leave in medium size pieces.
If using uncooked chicken, boil 1 whole chicken until meat falls from bones (about 1 hour).
Remove meat from bones and reserve broth to use in place of water in dressing. Steam cut-up broccoli for approximately 3 minutes; drain.
Place meat and broccoli in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soup and 1/2 cup milk and pour over meat/broccoli.
Prepare dressing with Pepperidge Farm dressing, melted margarine, egg and water.
Top meat/broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: better pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine pumpkin with dry ingredients. Slighlty beat egg yolks with egg whites, then blend with low-fat milk and pour evaporated skim milk.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 300° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Leave sausage out to soften.
Put all into large bowl and knead until all is blended well.
Make into small balls and chill. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until brown.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Serve with a toothpick.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Pour olive oil, vermicelli after draining and rinsing.
Add onions, green pepper, celery, pimientos and olives to pasta and then blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper together.
Add and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use food processor; add butter and bananas and process for 20 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients; process 10 seconds.
Put in pan.
Add nuts.
Bake for about 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cajun chicken(hot and spicy)
directions: Thoroughly wash chicken breasts (save juice chicken was contained in).
Place chicken breasts in large skillet.
Do not add any type of oil, or grease.
Sprinkle seasonings as listed. Turn chicken when one side has browned; repeat seasoning process. Add liquid, reserved from chicken.
(Sprinkle with water.)
Reduce heat when both sides are browned.
Check for doneness.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Coat chicken in flour and brown in oil.
Cook rice according to directions on box until it is almost done, but still juicy. Add the can of chicken soup and the 2/3 can of water.
Heat until the soup and water are heated.

title: happy day cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and shortening; mix well and add all other ingredients except flour.
Mix well; slowly add flour to just mix. Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry 'nana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in small pitcher. Add crushed pineapple, strawberries and mashed banana.

Pour approximately half the mixture into a Jel-N-Serve mold. Refrigerate until set. Reserve 2 tablespoons of sour cream for the garnish. Spread the remainder evenly over the gelatin. Spoon the remaining gelatin mixture evenly over the sour cream. Seal and chill until set. Before serving time, unmold onto the tray. Spoon the reserved sour cream into the design area, then carefully smooth.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dilly cheese bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, slice, cover with water and boil squash until tender. Drain off water in colander.
In large bowl, mix sour cream, chicken soup, carrots and onions, sauteed first with a little butter.
Mix well and fold in cooked squash.
Let set while you do the next step.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook the cake by the instructions on the box. When still hot, cut holes into the cake and pour pineapple juice and condensed milk all over the cake.
Refrigerate and let cool.
When cool, put cool whip as icing: sprinkle coconuts all over the icing.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups flour and next 7 ingredients. Beat at medium speed with an electric mixture 2 minutes. Gradually stir in 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and remaining 1 cup flour.
Cover and let rise in a warm place 85° free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: dressing for cucumbers and onions
directions: Mix well, then pour over sliced cucumbers and onions.
Chill for a few hours.
This also makes a good dip for fresh vegetables.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Combine ground sirloin and eggs; mix in salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon garlic powder.
Flatten on pizza pan, just like crust. Mix tomato sauce and 1 teaspoon garlic powder.
Spread on ground sirloin.
Layer pepperoni, salami, mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain before serving.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Melt in crock-pot on high the white chocolate and peanut butter.
Add Cap'n Crunch, Rice Krispies, marshmallows and pecans. Drop by tablespoonful on wax paper.
Makes 160 pieces.

title: shrimp and eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
To eggplant, add half same amount of water and dash of salt.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Grind remaining ingredients, except olive oil and bread crumbs, together with salt and dash of cayenne (or pepper).
Strain eggplant and press out water.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil in skillet.
Add all ingredients; cook for 10 minutes.
Put into casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven for 15 minutes.

title: brisket beef with onion sauce
directions: Cover meat with boiling water.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper. Simmer 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove to hot platter. Brown onions and garlic in fat.
Add flour, stir until blended. Pour over stock in which meat was cooked.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Parsley may be added.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice with sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Add coconut cream pudding and milk.
Mix well.
Put in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish and bake until brown on top.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Saute the bacon in a large saucepan or skillet.
In single layers, place the cabbage, onion, green pepper, hot pepper and tomato over bacon.
Pour water over vegetables and simmer cabbage mixture very slowly until cabbage is clear and tender.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Place pineapple in a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add blueberries.
Sprinkle sugar over blueberries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
(May use less cake mix if desired.)
Pour margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: old english rose potpourri
directions: In a large glass or glazed pottery bowl, gently mix together the ingredients in order given.
Stir gently.
Place the mixture in a brown paper bag, lined with wax paper.
Seal the top.
Put it in a dry, dark, cool place to cure, turning every two days or so with a wooden spoon.
After about two weeks, the mixture will be ready to put into a pretty bowl.
Try adding whole rose heads, in pink and red, on top for an extra flourish.

title: twenty minute fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix well and pat into the pie pan, shaping the crust on sides and bottom.
Let set in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight before using.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Beat whites, adding 1/2 cup sugar gradually.
Beat yolks, adding 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Fold yolk mixture into whites.
Add nuts, crackers and baking powder.
Bake in oiled oblong pan for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: apple date cake
directions: Mix well vanilla, eggs, oil and sugar. Add and blend flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Then add apples, dates, black walnuts and pecans. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar, flour, eggs, cinnamon, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add pie filling and nuts.
Stir just until mixed.
Turn batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Loaves freeze well.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: roy's taters
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Seed and core pepper and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Slice onions.
Layer potatoes, tomatoes, pepper and onions in greased 3-quart casserole (round is best).
Dot casserole with butter and season to taste.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at least 1 hour at 325° or until potatoes are tender.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Add vanilla.
Add oatmeal.
Mix flour, soda and powder.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix just until moist.
Add corn flakes and any or all of the optional ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 22 to 24 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor; set aside.
Combine sugar and jello in hot water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and drained pineapple juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, cranberries, celery, fruit and nuts.
Put in a mold.
Chill several hours.

title: "souvlakia" - shish kabobs
directions: Place meat cubes in a shallow dish.
Combine marinade of wine, vinegar, onion, sugar, garlic and oil.
Pour over meat cubes; marinate overnight.
Remove meat from marinade and place on skewers, alternating with meat, small onions and green pepper strips.
Broil over charcoals or in oven, basting often with marinade sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable bars
