directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet with the unrolled sheets of crescent rolls; pat and stretch to fit sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Cut melon in 1-inch slices.
Remove all green skin.
Remove all red part, leave only pale pink.
Cut strips into 1/2-inch pieces.
Pour boiling water over pieces.
Let stand overnight. Then drain and cover with fresh water.
Cook until barely tender. Make a syrup of remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over melon strips and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain again. Reheat drained syrup and pour over melon again.
Let stand another night.
On third morning, drain off syrup.
Pack in sterilized jars, reheat syrup again.
Pour over melon in jars and seal.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff at high speed on electric mixer. Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat without stirring until syrup forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Add slowly to egg whites, beating on high speed until mixture thickens and holds shape.
Stir in nuts with spoon; drop onto waxed paper.
Yield: 50 pieces.

title: potato tot casserole
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Empty bag of potato tots into baking dish. Mix together soups, ground beef and onions. Spread evenly over the top of potato tots. Spread Cheddar cheese over top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked fudge
directions: Cream eggs and sugar; add melted butter.
Sift flour and cocoa together and add to mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until crispy on top and soft inside at 350°.
Serve warm with scoop of ice cream and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa 1 1/2 minutes or to full boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and other ingredients. Beat well until thick.
Drop onto waxed paper to cool.

title: chocolate nutbutter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and peanut butter adding sugar gradually.
Add the eggs and vanilla beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients alternately with the milk, blending well after each addition. Drop by rounded tsp. onto ungreased baking sheets.
Press with fork to flatten and form a lattice design. (Put fork in water lightly before pressing so it does not stick
to the cookies.) Bake at 400 for 8 to 9 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cookies are still soft when done.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, butter, vinegar and salt.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until syrup reaches 270° or forms a brittle ball when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped corn, stirring until all kernels are covered.
Grease hands with butter and shape into balls.
Makes 12.
Do not double recipe.
It is better to make several small batches.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar,
flour,
cornstarch and cocoa.
Mix well. Beat eggs,
vanilla,
butter
and milk.
Add to dry ingredients and beat until
well
blended.
Add chopped walnuts and 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into
unbaked
pie shell.
Top with 1 inch additional coconut.
Bake
at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.
(I cook mine
in 300° for 10 minutes then on 350° for the remaining 30 minutes.)

title: braised beef
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, onion, apple, salt and pepper to meat.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook 15 minutes more.

title: quick salad dressing
directions: Mix and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve over green salad.

title: sharron's macaroni salad
directions: In blender, mix first 7 ingredients for dressing.
Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add onion rings, cucumbers, celery, carrots and peas.
Pour dressing over all and let marinate overnight.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top just before serving.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together Eagle Brand milk, water and instant pudding.
Mix well.
Let chill for 5 minutes.
Next, add vanilla flavoring and Cool Whip.
Stir all together until well blended.
Spread over cake.
Top with peaches.
Repeat again, ending with peaches on top.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in a large saucepan.
Bring it to a boil.
Remove the pan from the heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and cereal.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and macaroni.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
This can be cooked fast and serves 4.

title: play dough
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook until dough separates from side of pan.
Lay dough out on counter and knead until smooth.
You may separate into balls and color with 2 or 3 drops of food coloring.
Store in airtight bags in refrigerator indefinitely.
Enjoy!

title: creole carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots until tender; drain and cool.
Combine soup, sugar, salad oil and Worcestershire in saucepan; boil and stir to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
In 2-quart casserole, combine with vegetables and chill overnight.
Serve chilled. Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: windmill cookies
directions: You will need 30 popsicle sticks.

title: minty chocolate shake
directions: In a large pitcher, combine all ingredients, except mint sprigs.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir very vigorously.
Serve in tall chilled glasses; garnish with mint leaves.
Serves 6.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into small balls.
Roll balls in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon a little at a time.
Mix together, then add pumpkin.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 350°.
Cook 35 minutes.

title: seafood soup
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil in pot; add onions, garlic and celery until wilted.
Add tomatoes, Tabasco and saffron and cook over high heat for 4 minutes.
Add wine, water, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and cook for 15 minutes. Add fish, mussels and scallops.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and basil.
Serves 6.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix sugar, Kool-Aid, water and juice.
Before serving, add ginger ale.
Can be stored.
Freeze and thaw before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Coat biscuits with cinnamon mixture.
Arrange biscuits in layers.
Sprinkle with raisins and nuts.
Mix oleo and brown sugar.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Dissolve soda in part of buttermilk.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. This batter will keep in refrigerator for up to a month.
Just bake as needed.

title: cheese cake(reduced calorie)
directions: Cream the cream cheese with a little milk at a time until smooth; add pudding, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker; chill.
No baking; easy and good.

title: raisin broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Blend in last three.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: whole baked garlic
directions: Remove the outer layer of skins from the heads, exposing the cloves.
Place them in a small baking dish and pour the oil and butter over the bulbs.
Bake, uncovered in a 225° oven for 1/2 hour.
Baste; add 1/2 cup water to the dish.
Cover and bake another 1 1/2 hours or until bulbs are soft.
Serve with French bread and cheese; spread cheese on bread.
Break off a few bulbs of garlic and squeeze them out of their skins.
Lay on top of cheese.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven with enough water to cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When done, debone and place to side.
Mix other ingredients well and add chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon lust
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients into a dough.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix milk and pudding mix; spread over creamed cheese mixture.
Top with balance of Cool Whip.
Chill well.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix cubed bread, cheese and drained browned sausage.
Add drained mushrooms.
Put in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and dry mustard.
Mix milk with eggs and pour over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir together; let set 2 hours before serving.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine; mix well and press into the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Cook all together and pour in 2 baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites for frosting on pie. Brown.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar and softened cream cheese; add Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker shell. Top with blueberries.

title: chili supper casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in both cans of chili dinner, corn and cheese; heat until bubbling hot.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare muffin mix following package directions. Spoon half the batter in diagonal bands across top of casserole. Spoon remaining batter into 3 or 4 paper baking cup-lined muffin pans.
Bake both at 400° for 17 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until light and fluffy. Add peanut butter and milk.
Fold in 2 cups prepared Dream Whip.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 1 1/2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups oatmeal.
Then add vanilla, nuts and coconut. Stir and spoon on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: double chocolate dream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt in a small bowl. Set aside. Beat butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy. Beat in eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are puffed. Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: orange salad
directions: Put orange jello, tapioca pudding, vanilla pudding and water into saucepan.
Bring to a boil and slow boil for 5 minutes.
Cool well.
When cool, add oranges and Cool Whip.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Blend and chill.
Drop by spoonfuls into tassies muffin tins. Bake at 400° until brown (approximately 10 to 12 minutes).
Makes 4 dozen.
Can be frozen.

title: cole slaw
directions: Set cabbage and carrots aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Pour mixture over cabbage and carrots. Stir well and let set 24 hours.

title: beef log salami
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Put in the refrigerator and mix or knead each day for 5 days.
On the 5th day, shape into 4 logs and place on broiler pan on bottom rack of oven.
Bake 8 hours at 140°.
Turn every 2 hours.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix until combined.
Stir in nuts, currants and chopped cherries. Portion dough using measuring tablespoon.
Shape into balls.
Roll in crushed Kellogg's corn flakes cereal.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Top each with cherry quarter. Bake at 375°, about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheets.
Cool.
Yield:
about 5 dozen.

title: blackberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar and salt.
Beat well.
Add egg and lemon juice and beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread filling over cheese mixture.
Continue to bake at 400° for 20 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Cool.

title: no sugar pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and cream with margarine.
Add seasonings, pineapple, raisins and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients and add to liquids, mixing well but lightly.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a glass loaf pan.
As soon as it comes from the oven, cover with foil to keep in moisture.

title: punch
directions: Blend in blender, water, cranberry-orange relish and frozen orange juice. Put in freezer over night. Take out of freezer and allow it to get "slushy". Add 1 or 2 liters of 7-UP.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: *If using all-purpose flour, add 2 teaspoons baking powder.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine chicken, olives, green chilies, green onions and 1 cup of sauce.
Tear tortillas into bite-size pieces.
Place half of them in the bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chicken mixture over tortillas.
Put remaining tortilla pieces on top of chicken mixture.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas and top with cheeses.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zesty chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish combine uncooked rice, 1/2 can of onions and Italian seasoning.
Pour bouillon over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Place vegetables around chicken, covering rice.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken and rice are done.
Top with remaining onions; bake uncovered 1 to 3 minutes until golden brown.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Spread evenly on bottom of 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nut and coconut mixture.
Melt butter and mix with cream cheese.
Fold in confectioners sugar. Pour over cake mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: egg roll
directions: Cut the carrot, mushroom, and shrmp.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; mix well.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add cheese mixture and bacon to egg mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: fire balls
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften; mix well with horseradish.
Stir in chopped meat.
Roll in nuts after shaping into 24 balls.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: pineapple-date-nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: Combine pineapple and dates in small saucepan.
Cook over low flame, stirring constantly until dark and thick.
Stir in pecans. Turn off flame.
Cool 10 minutes. Pour date mixture into bowl. Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Add to date mixture.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients, just until moistened. Pour into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cover during last 15 minutes of baking time.
Cool completely, remove from pan.
Let stand overnight for better flavor and easier slicing.

title: caramel corn
directions: Wash the seeds to get rid of any pumpkin strings that might be stuck to them.
Put the seeds in a steamer (a pan with holes, inside another pan).
The idea is that you want the steam to cook the seeds, but you don't want the seeds to be in the water because that washes some of the vitamins out.
Keep the pot covered and cook for about 30 minutes.
Add more water when you need it.
Dump the seeds on a paper towel and pat them dry.
Spread them out on a cookie sheet.
Pour on a little vegetable oil, just enough to make the seeds shiny when you stir them around.
Sprinkle on some salt.
Put the seeds in an oven set at 300° for about 1/2 hour, until they are golden brown and crispy.

title: country captain
directions: Coat pieces of chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat.
Set aside.

title: date drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
(Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.)
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: tomato chow-chow
directions: Grind the first five ingredients together.
Soak and add salt; let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: mary's liver and onions
directions: Fry bacon until crispy; set aside.
In a plastic or paper bag, add flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly coat liver.
Using same grease from bacon, brown liver on both sides.

title: double chocolate mint chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Melt over hot (not boiling) water 3/4 cup Nestl| Toll House| mint flavored semi-sweet chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.* Cool to room temperature. In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla extract until creamy. Add melted morsels and egg; beat well. Gradually blend in flour mixture. Stir in remaining morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes. Allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheets; cool completely. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in about 2 tablespoons butter, then add meat and cook until brown, stirring frequently.
Drain. Add salt, tomato soup, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with cooked spaghetti in a greased 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh garden pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat and place in pizza pan.
Bake until brown and let cool.
Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese and minced onions.
Spread on top of crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pizzas.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs. Fold in flour, soda and salt in mixture until batter is smooth. Add chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
For chewy cookies, do not overbake.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, sugar and margarine.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax on top of stove.
Using toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate.
Place balls on wax paper.

title: almond tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in large container.
Add ice or ice ring.
Makes a gallon of punch.

title: fluffy dessert
directions: Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: kolache
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, salt and egg thoroughly.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add creamed mixture and 1 1/2 cups flour. Beat on low speed with electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise in warm place (85°) for about 1 1/2 hours.
If kitchen is cool, place dough on bowl of hot water and cover completely.
Stir down and put on well floured board.
Divide into 24 parts.
Shape each piece into a round ball.
Cover with cloth and let rest about 15 minutes.
Shape as desired and fill. Let rise 30 minutes until depression remains when touched lightly finger.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven about 15 to 18 minutes or until brown.
Brush with melted butter and dust lightly with powdered sugar.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in double boiler. Set aside to cool for 5 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, combine melted candy bars with whipped topping and pour into crust.
Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large bowl combine cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, sour cream and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat on medium until smooth.
Gradually add flour.
Add eggs and beat well.
In small bowl combine cocoa and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add oil, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 1/2 cups of cream cheese mixture.
Blend well.
Spoon plain and chocolate mixtures alternately into pan, ending with droplets of chocolate.
Swirl gently with spatula.
Bake 10 minutes.
Decrease temperature to 250° for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven door.
Turn off oven and leave in oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Sweetened peaches to taste.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Combine together butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture.
Spread in well greased 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies pulls away from pan.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk in bowl; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Arrange peaches over top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Toss lightly with apples.
Heap in pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Slit.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Divide burger into 5 to 6 patties.
Flatten each to approximately 6-inches.
Put approximately 1/3 cup stuffing in center of each patty.
Wrap meat around stuffing and mold into ball.
Meat does not have to completely cover stuffing.
Put the exposed stuffing side down in pan. Distribute balls evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach chicken
directions: Cut up frying chicken.
Dip in flour-salt mixture.
Brown chicken in thin layer of oil.
Remove from pan; drain pan leaving chicken bits.
Add orange juice, garlic clove (chopped) and nutmeg to frying bits and simmer.
Orange juice will reduce and thicken. Add chicken and sliced peaches.
Cover and cook for 35 minutes at medium heat.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order listed.
Let sauce simmer on the stove for about 1 hour and then add 1 pound to 1 1/2 pounds chipped ham per recipe.
Let meat and sauce simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: peanut butter ice cream squares
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cracker crumbs and sugar and put in melted butter. Stir well and press in bottom of pan.
Freeze for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add flour and buttermilk, a little at a time.
Mix oil, coconut flavoring and coconut.
Mix with a spoon. Pour in a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Mix all well.
Mix in fried bacon. Bake, covered, for 1 hour or more.
Uncover for 1/2 hour.

title: raw pear cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Punch top full of holes so icing will seep into cake.
Top with Buttermilk Icing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add corn.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Slowly stir in milk or cream and blend in butter. Combine with corn mixture (mix well).
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Pudding is done when knife is inserted in center and it comes out clean.

title: chicken escort
directions: Boil the fryer until tender, then debone it.
Crumble the crackers with 1/4 stick butter, melted, on the bottom of casserole.
Mix the soups and sour cream.
Layer crackers, chicken and soup mixture.
After about 2 layers, dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; reserve 1/2 cup, set aside. Add remaining ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Grease two 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Add batter and sprinkle crumbs (1/2 cup reserved) on top.
Also sprinkle cinnamon on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put in layers in the order given in crock-pot or heavy pan for top of stove or can be cooked in oven.
Season each layer with salt and pepper (if you like).
Put beef on top and mix tomato soup and water and pour over all.
Cover and cook until done (on top of stove approximately 45 minutes until vegetables are tender).

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish.
Mix first 6 ingredients together (rice and herbs in dry form).

title: hot crab dip
directions: Select grapes that are not too ripe.
Wash before pulling off stem; wash again.
Place in kettle.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Drain juice through cheesecloth.
Boil to reduce 1/3 or 1/2.
Measure, using 1 cup of juice to 1 cup of sugar. Bring to a hard boil and cook until jellies.
Pour into hot, sterilized glasses.
When cool, cover with paraffin.

title: oven barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken and muenster casserole
directions: Melt butter and brown onion.
Add soup, milk, salt and pepper. When hot, add chicken and noodles.
Pour into a casserole dish and cover.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese slices.
Return to oven just to melt cheese.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to make 1 1/2 quarts broth. Saute onions, peppers and drained mushrooms in margarine.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
When tender, add tomatoes and half the juice and Worcestershire sauce and cook until slightly thickened.
Add peas, mushrooms, onions and peppers.
Mix well. Add shredded cheese and stir until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped chicken.
Mix well.
Makes 3 casseroles (good to freeze now and cook later.)
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.
Add salad and you have a meal.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together all ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Pour contents into uncooked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: citrus poached orange roughy
directions: Arrange fish in a single layer in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Combine orange rind and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well. Pour mixture over fish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Remove fish from dish with a wide spatula and place on a serving dish. Sprinkle with green onions. Makes 4 servings. 130 calories, 3 grams cholesterol, 1.3 grams fat, 25.2 grams protein.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, meat, drain.
Add noodles, sauces and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Place in a baking dish and top with cheese and pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as usual and drain.
Add butter, tomato paste and water.
Mix well. Grate cheese or chop in food processor, then mix with macaroni.
Put macaroni in casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at about 325°.
Stir once during baking to mix melting cheese.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain well.
Add seasoning and cheese.
Stir over low heat until thoroughly melted.
Spread on bread and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. These will freeze and are great for appetizers.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs which have been sauteed in butter.
Blue cheese may be added to the crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serves 6.

title: condensed milk
directions: Beat until smooth in blender.
Yields 3 cups.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Simmer in crock-pot for 2 to 8 hours.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Parboil spareribs for 15 minutes with celery, onion and pepper; let water cover ribs.
Remove ribs and drain.
Baste with sauce.
Grill for 45 minutes over low fire, turning and basting frequently until done.

title: bubbling recipe for bubble wands(not for human consumption)
directions: Combine, shake and let settle 4 hours before using.
Store covered in refrigerator to extend shelf life, then allow to warm before using.
Joy and Karo work best.
Other brands do not work as well.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese and spinach.
Pour into a 2 quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: judy's sugar drizzle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide dough in half and chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Before rolling out dough, roll to 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
With cutters, cut in different shapes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: You will also need heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: tortellini and vegetable salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package.
Drain, rinse with cold water until cool.
In medium bowl, blend vegetable soup mix, mayonnaise, oil, lemon juice, basil, parsley and pepper.
Toss with tortellini, green onions and tomato.
Chill.
Makes approximately 4 cups.

title: miniature quiches
directions: Form pie crust into balls.
Place into greased muffin pan and press into shell shapes. Add grated cheese and onion.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese and Tostitos) and cook until well mixed.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Cut in as pie crust and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: barbecue
directions: Cut roast into small and medium cubes.
Salt and pepper meat, then mix all remaining ingredients together.
Pour the mix over the meat.
Cook at 400° for about 3 hours.

title: alberta's green beans
directions: Drain the green beans.
Fry bacon and set aside.
Add onion to bacon drippings.
Add green beans and chili sauce.
Heat thoroughly and add bacon just before serving.

title: porch supper braids
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
In a large bowl combine margarine, sugar, salt, and milk.
Let sit until the mixture is warm, not hot.
Add egg, well beaten.
Then add the yeast mixture. GRADUALLY blend in sifted flour.
Cover and let stand for ten minutes.
For five to seven minutes, knead dough on a lightly floured board until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl and cover. Let rise in a warm place until dough doubles in bulk.
Allow 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Next, place dough on a floured board.
Divide dough into twelve pieces.
Pat each piece into a rectangle, 4 x 3 inches.
Vertically cut into three strips.
Braid, sealing ends. Place on greased pan.
Brush tops of braids with beaten egg or cream.
Sprinkle with poppy or sesame seeds.
Let rise in a warm place until size doubles (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 400 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry fork.
Combine peel, juice and egg.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix by hand just to moisten.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter or bacon grease. Add eggplant and tomatoes. Stir until it looks like scrambled eggs. Stir in cheese and 3/4 cup crumbs. Pour in baking dish. Add rest of crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Bake chicken in baking dish at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat and add barbecue mixture; bake 30 minutes longer.
Stir.

title: sex in a pan
directions: To make the crust, blend pecans, flour and oleo.
Press into a 13 x 9 inch
pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes and let cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and one container of cool whip together.
Spread over crust. Mix pudding and milk. Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread other container of cool whip over pudding mixture and top with chopped pecans.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Work dough well with the hands until it can be handled like pie pastry.
Break into small pieces and roll between the hands into cocoons.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° until very delicate brown.
Remove from oven; roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
When cool, roll in sugar again.
Yield: approximately 3 dozen.

title: poor man's cake
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to raisin mixture.
Add nuts.
Place in 2 medium loaf pans or 1 regular size.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water.
Drain, mash and add other ingredients, holding back 1/2 of stuffing.
Mix well and put in 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1 stick oleo and mix with remaining stuffing and use as topping for casserole.

title: nut and poppy seed roll
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in milk. Let rise. Rub the butter into the flour and add slightly beaten egg yolks and the yeast. Mix well and divide the dough in two parts. Let rise while mixing the poppy seed filling and walnuts together. Roll out dough and spread with filling. Roll up dough as you would a jelly roll. Let rise for 1/2 hour. Brush with egg whites. Bake 350 degree for 30 or 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Butter buns and put mixture on buns. Wrap in foil.
Place in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well blended.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of batter to make each patty.
Cook until browned on each side.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Heat sauerkraut until hot.
(Do not boil.)
Drain and add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In separate bowl, mix together flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
In another bowl, mix carrots, apple, coconut, dates and nuts.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla; add fruit to this mixture.
Stir well.
Add the dry ingredients to this; stir just until all is moistened.
Fill muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(from ina)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Beat eggs.
Add oil, brown sugar and zucchini and mix well.
Stir in flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans; cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear in color. Mix 1 to 2 tablespoons flour to coat onions well.
Put water and bouillon cubes in pot and heat until cubes are dissolved.
May want to add garlic powder and parsley.
Add onions and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Spoon
mixture	and batter alternately in pan.	Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's lasagna(two-layer)
directions: Boil noodles for 10 minutes (4 noodles per layer).
Brown meat; drain.
Mix meat and spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer; heat through.
Put in layers:

title: meat pie with mashed potato
directions: Cut meat into small cubes and brown slightly in frying pan. Then place into a greased casserole.
Spread cooked corn over top; spread soup over top, adding 1/4 can of water.
Spread mashed potatoes over top, dot with butter and bake in 400° oven until brown.
Note:
You may also use peas and carrots in place of corn.

title: kahlua(liqueur)
directions: Simmer sugar and water for 5 minutes or longer for thicker syrup.
Let cool.
Put instant coffee and water in saucepan. Bring to boil.
Let cool.
Mix together.
Add vanilla and alcohol. Makes about 5 fifths of liquor.

title: savory stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Steam Vidalia onions by wrapping each one in a damp paper towel.
Microwave at 100% for about 10 minutes or until tender. Spoon out inside pulp, leaving three outer layers of onions.
You should have a circular opening.
Place in a casserole dish.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients except garnish.
Place stuffing mixture equally into each of the steamed Vidalias. Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes at 100% until well heated.
Garnish each Vidalia onion with 5 boiled shrimp around top edge of onion. Sprinkle center with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Beat salt and egg together until fluffy; mix with other ingredients until it pulls away from sides of dish.
Drop on baking sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of pea soup
directions: Cook peas in 1 cup water.
Puree.
Add peas and seasonings to stock, except for chervil.
Slowly add the half and half and the milk.
Add chervil.
Heat carefully.
Do not allow to boil!

title: crisco icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool.
Add Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high.
Add pork; stir-fry until well browned.
Add peppers; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, cornstarch, garlic powder, ginger and pineapple chunks in juice; add to skillet.
Bring to a boil. Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve pork mixture over rice.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time, 25 minutes.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Combine dates and soda.
Pour boiling water over and let cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and add to date mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and stir well. Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pasta and roasted red pepper sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain and keep warm. Meanwhile, heat the oil in a nonstick saucepan over medium-low heat. Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in roasted peppers and basil; cook about 1 minute longer. Add broth; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes longer. Remove from heat and stir in half-and-half. Puree the sauce in a food processor or blender. Pour sauce over the pasta and toss to coat.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hot plate chili
directions: In heavy pan with a tight lid, saute the garlic buds in the oil.
Remove the garlic and add ground beef.
(If desired, sprinkle garlic powder and steak tenderizer on meat.)
Cook slowly until the red is gone from the meat and has a slight crust.
Add tomatoes and beans and stir together lightly.
Add seasonings to taste.
Simmer 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with crackers.
Chili is better after it has cooled and the fat has been removed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon layer cake
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, then flour, then raisins, dates, then lemon rind and juice.
Bake in four 9-inch cake pans, greased and lined with paper.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: egg substitute
directions: Mix well.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Use 1/4 cup for 1 egg.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil can of crushed pineapple.
Mix jello into pineapple. Cool, then add 2 cups buttermilk.
Let almost jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chicken noodle soup(also chicken rice soup)
directions: Wash chicken good; cover with water and cook until chicken is done.
Take the chicken out and bone it.
Cut up and put back in broth.
Add noodles and cook until the noodles are done.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drained can fruit.
Combine fruit.
Mix in walnuts, then mix in coconut.
Fold in sour cream.
Serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add rice and water into pot.
Cover.
At medium heat, cook until all water is absorbed.
Take off stove.
Add sugar and milk. Cook on medium heat.
When it starts to boil, lower heat to a simmer (very low simmer).
It takes about 1 hour to cook.
(Stir 4 or 5 times during the hour.)
Beat the eggs, vanilla and half and half.
Set aside until all milk is absorbed.
Put the heat on high. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and half and half.
Stir 60 times until it bubbles.
It will look loose.

title: three bean salad
directions: *One extra can of either green or wax beans to take up extra juice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve in round pumpernickel loaf.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, sift or stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine, shortening and sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: daddy's custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs slightly with rotary beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar, chips, margarine and milk.
Cook in microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove and add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.
Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased dish.

title: decorative holly berry cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat and add green food coloring and cornflakes.
Stir until cornflakes are well coated.
Form cornflakes into rounds and press in the middle.
Place red cinnamon candies in middle.
Use on cookie trays for decoration or just eat for special Christmas treats!
Refrigerate.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Mix together and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff; add 1 cup brown sugar.
Spread on top of cake and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: tropical candy clusters
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt milk chocolate chips, semi-sweet chocolate chips, condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, pineapple and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper lined baking dish.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift 3 times with salt, soda and spices.
Cream butter until smooth.
Add sugar and egg and cream until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and beat vigorously for 2 minutes longer.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately in 3 or 4 portions, beginning and ending with flour and beating well after each portion.
Turn batter into a greased 11 x 7 x 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on cake rack for 5 minutes, then turn out on rack and invert.
Serve warm or cold.
If glass dish is used, bake at 325°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter; add onion, oregano, mushrooms, liquids, then rice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Bake in covered dish 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Boil, drain and mash squash. Add eggs, flour, sugar and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Enjoy!

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Chop up chuck roast into bite size pieces. Salt and pepper and flour and brown in 2 tablespoons of oil. Add onion and cook until transparent. Add beef broth until it covers meat. Add 2 whole cloves, 2 bay leaves and paprika until soup is red looking, about 2 to 4 tablespoons. Cover and bring to boil, then turn down heat to simmer. Simmer for 2 hours or until roast is tender. Cook wide noodles and serve goulash over the noodles. Makes 6 servings. Preparation time: 2 hours.

title: fruit stuffed pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over chops.
Combine bread cubes, apple, cheese, raisins, butter, orange juice, salt and cinnamon. Stuff mixture into pockets.
Press edge of pockets together to seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: e-z quiche
directions: Mix half and half, eggs and flour well.
Line pie shell with Swiss cheese; fill bottom with ham.
Add egg mixture and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: spiced fruit
directions: Pour juice off everything (save the pineapple juice).
Cook the pineapple juice with butter, lemon juice, brown sugar, ginger and cinnamon until hot.
Pour over fruit and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring several times to coat the
fruit while cooking.

title: veg-all salad
directions: First, heat in pan until sugar is dissolved the sugar, Crisco oil, vinegar, pepper and salt.
Drain all vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate.
The longer it sits the better it gets.

title: hot crab bread
directions: Combine crabmeat, mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, lemon juice and garlic salt. Chill. Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Place on foil or on baking sheet.
Spread cut sides with margarine. Arrange cheese slices on bottom half of bread and top with crab mixture.
Cover with top half of bread.
Carefully cut crosswise into serving pieces 1 inch or wider.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: terry's crab imperial
directions: Blend the cream, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and egg yolk in the mayonnaise.
Set aside 1/4 of the mixture.
Add crab meat to the remaining 3/4 of the mixture and blend lightly.
Divide the crab meat into 4 glass crab dishes or 4 real crab shells, cleaned thoroughly.
Top with the reserved mayonnaise mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until thoroughly heated and lightly browned, approximately 20 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crumble crackers in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Melt butter and pour over crackers and mix well.
Smooth out.
Mix ice cream, pudding and milk until smooth.
Put on top of cracker mix.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: quick chicken
directions: Brown chicken, remove and drain pan.
Add celery soup, milk, parsley, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Cover, cook 10 minutes. Serve with rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt, eggs and milk together.
Add to hot fat and bake at 450° until puffy and brown on edges.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Coat a
medium saucepan with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and saute 3 minutes or until tender.
Add flour, mustard and salt; stir well and cook an additional minute.
Remove from heat; gradually add milk and broth, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add cheeses and pepper, stirring until cheeses melt. Stir in sour cream.
Combine cheese mixture and potatoes; stir well.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix sugar, buttermilk, soda dissolved in milk, Karo and butter until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Beat until creamy. Add nuts. Drop from spoon when begins to harden.

title: sausage cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Brush all sides with Proverbs 31:6.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Add all ingredients together in large pot.
Cook on high about 15 minutes or until pasta is soft.
Serve.

title: gelled mango salad
directions: Blend mango and cream cheese.
Heat water and juice to boiling; add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Add lime juice. Combine with mango-cream cheese mixture and blend well.
Chill until set in mold or glass casserole dish.
Serves 8.

title: burnt cream fudge
directions: Put 1 cup sugar in a pan and melt completely.
Then pour 1 cup cold water into it.
While it is melting, mix 2 cups sugar, canned milk and butter in bowl until dissolved.
Pour into dissolved sugar and water.
Cook until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Beat by hand until it starts to thicken.
Pour in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge beef in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in pan over high heat.
Add 1/2 can of consomme and 1/2 can of water. Cook until tender (add more water if needed).
Add onion, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and soups and mix well.
Place in large flat baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and bake 30 more minutes.
Cook rice according to directions, substituting the remaining consomme for equal amount. Serve over rice.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour and then add milk (slowly). Cook till thick.
Simmer 2 or 3 minutes then add cheese, salt, pepper, pimento beans and corn.
Pour into greased dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Then add bread crumbs (cover the top) and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 45
minutes to 1 hour on 350 degrees.

title: julia's gingersnaps
directions: Heat molasses, then cool.
Add Crisco, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add well beaten egg.
Then beat in flour and baking powder.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll thin and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bell pepper in a skillet under low heat until onion and bell pepper are soft.
Drain off excess grease.
Add kidney beans and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Pour prepared mashed potatoes over top, covering well.
Bake 15 minutes or until potatoes begin to brown at 375°.

title: rumanian cabbage soup
directions: Put all ingredients (except the last 4) in a large kettle. Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Shred cabbage coarsely and add with sugar and vinegar to soup.
Continue simmering 1 1/3 hours or until meat is very tender. Skim off fat. Remove meat and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cut marrow from the bones and return with meat to soup.
Add more seasoning if necessary.
Serve hot with sprinkling of dill.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: sour cream corn casserole
directions: Stir together and pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Then sprinkle on top:
1 cup grated Cheddar Cheese and 1 Tbsp. Peppers chopped (optional).
Bake 50 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: dreamy pan cake
directions: Bake cake in a large dripping pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Microwave on Full power for 15 minutes.
Turn once during cooking time.
May also be baked in the oven at 350° until set.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 3/4 stick of butter and cheese together in microwave. Mix with drained vegetables.
Mix in soup undiluted.
Melt remaining butter and mix with crumbled crackers.
Pour mixture into baking dish and top with cracker mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: brownies with a crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1 cup flour and sugar.
Cut into margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine chocolate chips, half & half and butter in sauce pan - on medium heat, stir till chocolate chips melt.
Add sugar, beat well. Set sauce pan in ice water and beat until it holds shape and loses gloss.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients first and then combine eggs and milk. Lightly stir in melted butter; do not overmix, will become dry. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: bubble recipe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use bubble wands, empty spools, bottomless paper cups, berry baskets, etc. to "blow bubbles." Food coloring may be added to the mixture.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: nut-cracker sweets
directions: Melt chocolate in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in cinnamon.
Fold in cashews and crackers.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen candies.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Heat milk and margarine.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with hot milk and margarine.
Add flavorings.
Bake in 2 greased and floured cake pans or tube pan.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil, but do not boil.
Quickly add peanut butter and blend.
Quickly add cornflakes and blend.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: tater tots
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix with sour cream and hot sauce.
Keep refrigerated till serving.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in glass pie plate. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: garden wild rice
directions: Rinse wild rice in 3 changes of hot water.
Drain.
Combine rice, 2 1/2 cups water and bouillon granules in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 50 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain and set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and diced onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, garlic salt or powder and mushrooms; simmer for at least 1 hour.
Prepare lasagna noodles as directed on package, using 2 tablespoons oil in boiling water to prevent sticking together. Pour small amount of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Lay one layer of noodles; cover with sauce.
Then, using a teaspoon, distribute 1/2 of the Ricotta cheese on the sauce.
Cut 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese into chunks; distribute likewise.
Repeat noodle layer, sauce layer, then Ricotta and Mozzarella layers.
Lay remaining noodle layer; cover with sauce.
Shred the least 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese to cover top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fiesta pork chops
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole and arrange chops on the bottom. Mix soup mix, pepper and rice.
Spread over chops.
Mix water, catsup and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chops and rice mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours.
(Add water if needed, while baking.)
Set oven temperature to 350°.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Combine beef, beans, oregano, cumin and garlic powder.
Place 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread half of beef mixture over noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles, beef mixture and remaining noodles.
Combine water and salsa.
Pour over all.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are tender.
Combine sour cream, onion and olives.
Spoon over casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, then combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, coconut, marshmallows and nuts. Mix sour cream and sugar together. Stir into fruit mixture. Chill 2 hours.

title: pepper jack stuffed chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut cheese into strips.
Place cheese down center of chicken.
Fold chicken over cheese and secure with toothpicks.
Rub with taco seasoning.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Put in a greased 8x8-inch dish.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour and pepper in a dish. Dredge chicken in flour mixture and shake off extra flour. In a large pan, heat 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat. Add chicken and cook until lightly browned, about 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Remove chicken and keep warm. Combine garlic, mushrooms and 2 tablespoons butter and cook until lightly browned. Add wine and bring to a light boil. Stir well. Add cream and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Return chicken to pan. Cover with Marsala sauce. Let simmer a few minutes. Serve over pasta. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: two chicken - broccoli casseroles
directions: Lightly grease 2 (2-quart) shallow baking dishes or 8-inch square pans.
Whisk undiluted soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in medium size bowl until well blended.
Put 1/2 of the broccoli in each pan.
Top with 1/2 of the chicken.
Pour soup mixture over each; spread to cover.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until lightly brown.
Scatter onions over top.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes more until onions are lightly brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Crumble graham crackers very fine. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Add sugar, baking powder and flavoring. Beat thoroughly. Add cracker crumbs and nuts; mix well. Put in buttered pie plate and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool. Top with whipped cream and chill for 1 hour.

title: rosie's orange cookies
directions: Beat sugar, oleo and egg to a smooth batter.
Add flour, baking powder, sour cream, baking soda, orange juice, rind and salt.
Beat all together.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven, cool and frost with frosting.
Add 1 teaspoon grated rind.

title: cream of cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add cabbage, onion and potato.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add broth and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except salt in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and turn down to low immediately.
Simmer for several hours or until mixture gets thick, stirring occasionally, and mashing tomatoes against sides of pan with spoon.
Add salt to taste.
If a sweeter dish is desired, add more sugar.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil until well blended.
Add nuts, chips or raisins.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 - 12 minutes.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well.
Fold in milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Drop from tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In a large saucepan, combine cranberries, brown sugar, raisins, celery, apple, 1/2 cup water, walnuts, ginger, lemon juice, onion salt and cloves.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Store, covered, in the refrigerator.
Serve chilled.
Top with walnut half, if desired.
Makes 3 cups.

title: grilled quail
directions: Rinse quail thoroughly with cold water. Pat dry. Place a jalapeno pepper into body cavity of each quail.
Wrap 1 bacon slice around each quail and secure with a wooden pick. Place quail in a large shallow dish.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie crust shells. Sprinkle with reserved onions and a little paprika and parsley for color.
Bake at 350° about 90 minutes until golden brown and bubbling over.

title: party punch
directions: Make ice ring for punch bowl by overlapping orange slices and placing cherries in a ring mold.
Add a small amount of lemonade to the mold.
Freeze.
Add more lemonade to top of mold and freeze. Combine all liquids and place mold in punch bowl.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour and soda together; add alternately with sour cream.
Begin and end with flour.
Mix in flavorings at low speed.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 to 20 minutes.

title: watermelon rind
directions: Cook and stir over low heat until rind is tender and is a thick consistency.
Serve over sherbet or vanilla ice cream.

title: coconut date bars
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add coconut and dates.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
After cooling, cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers. Pour mixture over crackers. Mix well. Set 1 hour.

title: haystack casserole
directions: Brown and season ground beef.
In a casserole or crock-pot, place a layer of sliced onions, carrots and potatoes on top of ground beef.
Empty the soup (undiluted) on top of potatoes.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300° or 6 hours on low in crock-pot.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in 6-quart pot or bigger.
Put in onions and garlic.
Saute for about 10 minutes.
Then add shallots and celery. Saute 10 minutes.
Then add bell peppers and parsley.
Continue to cook until tender, but not breaking up.
Drain all water out of chopped tomatoes and mushrooms.
Then add tomatoes and mushrooms to pot.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Then add shrimp.
Let them start to cook.
Then add all seasoning.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Then add 1/2 cup water and cornstarch.
Cook 10 minutes more and serve over rice or linguine noodles.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in container (I use a skillet).
Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla.
Crush wafers and mash bananas; stir together.
Pour the thickened filling over wafers and bananas and stir.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar.
Beat and pour on top of mix.
Bake until browned.

title: stockpile spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato paste in a 2-quart glass measuring cup.
Cover with plastic wrap, venting at one corner.
Microwave on High (100%) power 15 to 18 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
In food processor or electric blender, process one-third of the quantity with 1 can tomato paste until smooth. Repeat with remaining vegetables and tomato paste.
Freeze in 2-cup amounts to use for spaghetti, lasagna or pizza.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until nice and hot.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa very good. Add butter and eggs; beat well. Add milk, salt and vanilla. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable luncheon salad
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin, softened in cold water.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to soup mixture. Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 16 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix flour and cornstarch in a cup.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the cream cheese until fluffy.
In a blender, cream 1/2 of the cottage cheese adding 2 eggs.
Pour into the cream cheese. Cream the other half of the cottage cheese and 2 eggs. Add to the cream cheese along with the lemon juice and vanilla.
Slowly add the sugar, flour and cornstarch mixture.
Add melted butter and sour cream.
Pour into a 9-inch spring pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and let it set in the oven for 2 hours. Remove to room temperature and refrigerate.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water and then juices and mashed bananas.
Freeze overnight.
Stir and put in freezer until ready to use.
Thaw.
Put in punch bowl and add pop.
Serves 50.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all other ingredients. Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Grease pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 of coconut on bottom of pan.
Bake cake as directed.
Remove from oven and pour milk over hot cake. Cool and spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle coconut over.

title: iced spiced coffee
directions: Cover mixture of first 3 ingredients and let stand 2 hours. Heat water and sugar to dissolve.
Using 1/2-gallon glass container, strain coffee.
Add sugar syrup.
Add about 3/4 pint of Coffee Rich or light cream (to taste).

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add last the black-eyed peas and grated Cheddar.
Pour into a well-greased hot #8 large iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Great reheated in microwave.

title: skillet cornbread with hot dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: patsy's punch
directions: Use a small amount of ice, depending on whether liquids are cold.
Serves 16 to 20 people.

title: pecan crescent cookies
directions: *Or can use all real butter.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Combine egg, salt and sugar in a bowl; add milk gradually, then add coconut and mix.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Decrease heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bake 1 unfilled pricked pie crust until very lightly browned at 400°. Combine margarine, broth, evaporated milk and flour in saucepan. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add chicken, eggs, salt and pepper. Add additional broth if too thick. Pour in lightly browned pie crust. Cover with 2nd pie crust and seal edges of filled pie crust. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is browned.

title: sunday morning rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in greased (or sprayed) Bundt pan. Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Cook butter, sugar and cinnamon over medium heat.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Cool slightly, then pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil and let sit out overnight.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large bowl.
Add milk and margarine (don't mix).
Cook for 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Add vanilla extract and nuts; stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered dish and cool until firm.

title: jalapeno quiche
directions: Beat eggs, mayonnaise and milk; fold in remaining ingredients, except for jalapenos. Pour into pie shell; top with peppers. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean when inserted in middle.

title: candied nuts
directions: Get everything ready first.

title: best ever punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add orange juice concentrate, water, lemonade concentrate, water, pineapple juice, juice of lemons and bananas.
Freeze.
About 1/2 hour before serving, place frozen base in punch bowl.
Let thaw until slushy.
Add 2 quarts cold ginger ale.
Serve.
Makes 50 to 60 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: indian relish
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients.
Cover with 1/2 cup salt and let stand overnight; drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to boil and simmer 3 hours.
Put in sterile hot jars; no processing needed.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and dried onions and bring to a boil.
Mix half of this mixture with the rest of ingredients to make meat loaf, then pour the rest of the mixture over the meat loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with ground beef.
Top with 1 pound grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
This will melt in while simmering for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven at 400 degrees.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 of onions.
Place in sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Combine chocolate and peanut butter morsels in pan.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes over low heat or until morsels are melted.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store airtight and allow them to cool.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: dream bars
directions: Combine the
first
4 ingredients and spread in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken surprise
directions: Place toast in buttered 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Put one serving of cooked green beans on each slice.
Top with pieces of cooked chicken.
Mix can of soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine bananas, oil and vanilla.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly with fork.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: quick-and-easy strawberry jam
directions: Use any containers 1 pint or smaller that have tight fitting lids.
Wash, scald and drain containers and lids or use automatic dishwasher with really hot rinse water (150° or higher).

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; add water to make 2 cups.
Heat juice to boiling; add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add Coke and fruit.
Put in 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with salad dressing, cream cheese or whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar cutout cookies
directions: With mixer, cream sugar, butter, egg, soda, sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Add flour, mixing well by hand.
Chill.
Roll on floured board and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 375° until brown around edges.
Colored sugar can be sprinkled on dough before baking or cookies can be cooled and iced or decorated.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Cook rigatoni noodles per directions on box; drain. Mix hamburger and noodles together.
Add spaghetti sauce and cut up pepperoni.
(May substitute mushrooms or Canadian bacon or your favorite for the pepperoni.)
Stir all ingredients and put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through (approximately 30 minutes).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip
together yams, sugar, margarine, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Layer
this
mixture
in	a
buttered,
shallow casserole
dish with sliced bananas and coconut.
Repeat until all ingredients
are used.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and top with corn flakes.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 20 minutes or until topping forms a crust.

title: vacation bible school wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon honey in large bowl with 1/2 cup water (warm 110°).
Add oil, 1/4 cup honey, salt and 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix well and add egg.
Add whole wheat flour and white flour.
Stir well and knead a few times until smooth and satiny. Roll out on floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double (30 minutes).
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix in large pan; put in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: french peas
directions: In a saucepan, cook the green onions and lettuce in oil over low heat for 5 minutes. Combine flour with water or broth. Add to lettuce mixture and stir until thickened.
Put in the cooked peas, sliced water chestnuts and seasonings.
Heat through and serve.

title: italian spaghetti squash
directions: Heat organic tomato sauce with Italian seasoning.
Add the remaining ingredients, raw, as desired.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Fry mushrooms, green peppers, onion and celery in butter or oil.
Add flour and milk and cook until thick.
Add chicken. Serve over mashed potatoes or biscuits.

title: lamb stew
directions: Put lamb pieces in pot.
Add water and simmer 45 minutes.
Can add onion at this time and little garlic powder.
When lamb is just about done, add chunks of potatoes and carrots.
Add salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer about 15 minutes more.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of cooking oil. Add ground meat; season with salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat (300° in electric skillet) until meat is crumbly; may have to separate meat with fork.
Drain grease; add tomato sauce, mushrooms (if desired), and Italian seasoning to taste.
Simmer for at least one hour.
Serve hot over cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pap's juice
directions: Squeeze fruits into one-gallon pitcher.
Add cold water to make approximately one gallon of juice.
Add sugar to taste.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° to 450° until lightly brown.

title: chocolate sprinkle cookies
directions: Melt together sour milk, chocolate and brown sugar until smooth.
Cool and then add vanilla.
In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar, then add egg.
Mix dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Alternate chocolate mixture and dry ingredients into cream mixture.
Add the sprinkles and drop by rounded teaspoon. Makes about 40 cookies.
Bake cookies in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in casserole dish 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: finnish pasty mix or filling(good)
directions: Mix potatoes, carrots, rutabagas and onions together.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Mix well until meat is evenly distributed. Place 1 cup mixture into a 9-inch pastry crust.
Shape into half moon and bake on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 375° or until vegetables are soft.
Test by inserting fork into pasty.
Makes 10 to 12 pasties.
Make pie crust.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time,
beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
To the batter, add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavorings and beat well.
Bake in a large greased Bundt or tube at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Glaze.

title: marinated carrots (2)
directions: Mix onion, green pepper, sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Add tomato soup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots and mix.

title: friendship cake
directions: Stir together in a gallon container (not plastic).
Stir every day with a wooden spoon.
Keep lid on loosely.

title: golden fruit cake
directions: Chop and dredge all fruits and nuts with flour.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture with sweet milk. Add almond extract, fold in dredged fruit and nuts.
Fold in carefully, egg whites.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: chicken and cheese rollatini
directions: Cut chicken to make 4 half breasts.
Flatten each half by pounding on a cutting board with a meat pounder.
Divide Provolone among cutlets, placing cheese in center of each, then rolling so cheese is inside.
Combine oil and lemon juice in a dish; add salt and pepper if using.
Combine crumbs and Romano in another dish. Dip each chicken roll first in the oil-juice mixture, then in the crumb-cheese mixture until lightly coated.
Arrange rolls on a shallow, nonstick baking tray sprayed until slick with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Makes 4 rollatini; contains 275 calories each.

title: choucroute
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, pricking sausage to release fat.
Turn occasionally until done.
Drain.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix together the first 10 ingredients.
Fold in the apples, raisins and walnuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Smooth into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 5 ingredients; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moist.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: honey chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Cream shortening with sugar and honey until fluffy. Add egg yolk and chocolate; beat thoroughly. Add sifted ingredients and liquids alternately in small amounts. Beat egg white until stiff and fold into batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Spread fig filling between layers and ice with caramel icing. Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: spiced tea
directions: Store in airtight container.
Add 2 teaspoons or to taste to a cup of hot water and mix.

title: texas fudge cake
directions: Melt oleo. Add water and cocoa and bring to a boil. Add rest of ingredients. Place in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Spread icing on cake while hot.

title: pea picker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 25 minutes or longer.
Cool completely.

title: do-ahead party potatoes
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream, onion salt and pepper; beat mixture into potatoes until smooth and fluffy.
Season to taste.
Place in 2-quart greased, covered casserole in refrigerator.

title: pork tenderloin with potatoes
directions: Brown pork tenderloins in garlic oil.
Precook potatoes until partially done.
Place both tenderloins and potatoes, halved, in ovenproof baking dish.
Add more garlic and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and soda together in a mixing bowl.
Add egg and pineapple with liquid. Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 350` for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cornish scones("teatime" dessert)
directions: Mix; place onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, split and spread with butter.
Makes 16.

title: zucchini pickled
directions: Cut unpeeled zucchini into very thin slices (like cucumbers). Peel onions and slice thin.
Cover vegetables with water.
Add salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand 1 hour.
Return to heat and boil 3 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Adjust lids.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 4 pints.

title: polynesian rice
directions: Melt margarine; add rice and coat well.
Add beef consomme and water.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add soy sauce, onions, almonds and mushrooms.
Toss well.

title: cranberry hot punch
directions: For strong tea, simmer 2 family tea bags in 4 cups water while preparing other ingredients.
In large 6-quart pan, put water, sugar, red hots and cloves (which have been put into tea bag or tied in a cloth).
Heat until red hots dissolve, then remove clove bag.
Add cranberry juice, orange and lemon juices and tea.
Serve hot.

title: favorite yellow cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions.
Combine remaining ingredients at room temperature.
Spread all over cake. Sprinkle on top coconut and crushed English walnuts.
Very good.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a dish. Mix sugar, flour and milk; pour over butter. Pour peaches in center and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and melted butter.
