Place pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour filling over them (can put pecans on top if desired).
Place pie on solid metal cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until filling is set.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Stir in pecans and coconut.
Spread in prepared pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place by large spoonfuls on top of cake batter.
Swirl mixture through cake with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice and almond casserole
directions: Melt butter.
In casserole dish, add butter and other ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in covered dish at 325°.
Set timer for 45 minutes and stir once.
Reset timer and bake for another 45 minutes.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add beer and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Cut cod, perch, haddock or favorite fish into 1 1/2 or 2-ounce pieces or chunks.
Coat each with batter and fry in hot oil.

title: peach cottage pudding
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening, egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with spicy peach sauce.

title: challah bread
directions: In large, glass bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon of the sugar in water.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Add salt, remaining sugar, oil and 4 eggs; mix well.
Add 3 cups of flour at a time until you have a firm dough.

title: ruby's cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook until cheese is melted and serve.

title: molded vegetable relish
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar and onion.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in other 4 vegetables and chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and garlic salt until smooth. Add olives.
Form into ball, or leave in dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in sweet potatoes.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, mix thoroughly ground beef, 1/4 cup soup, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into 6 oval patties.

title: apples on a stick
directions: Will need 6 wooden skewers.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add both packages of dry rice mixture, chili powder, tomatoes and water.
Stir and cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with shredded cheese and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: n'orlns style milk punch
directions: Put all ingredients in shaker except nutmeg.
Pour into old fashioned glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry torte or blueberry torte
directions: Graham cracker crust:
Mix well, line in a 9 x 13 pan, leaving some for the topping.

title: real garlic bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on bread.
Wrap in foil and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Unwrap and brown under broiler.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes in large skillet until cooked halfway.
Add onion and salt.
When cooked, beat eggs and pour over mixture.
Cook until egg is like scrambled.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients.
Bake in muffin pan at 350° until brown.

title: applesauce pudding cake
directions: Spread applesauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix on top of this mixture. Cut 1 stick of butter into pats and place on top and then sprinkle again with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add salt, nutmeg and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake until well done in center, when toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Heat mushrooms with 1 stick butter.
Combine with 1 cup water and stuffing, tossing lightly until crumbs are moistened.
Spoon stuffing mixture onto the flank steak (almost to the edges).
Roll jellyroll fashion with the meat fibers running lengthwise.
Secure with skewers and lace with poultry lacing.

title: 5 minute tomato aspic salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add tomato sauce and other ingredients.
Blend.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Place on crisp greens with mayonnaise.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground beef with onions. Put the remaining ingredients in a large soup pot. Add beef and onions. Cook. Serve with Mexican cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Put bananas through sieve; add lemon juice, then add to mixture.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and mix well with banana mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: All ingredients can be mixed directly in freezer can.

title: green beans baked in sour cream
directions: Heat butter to bubbling.
Add onion and saute until soft. Sprinkle flour over; stir and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and sour cream.
Mix well, then fold into cooked beans. Turn into a 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with extra margarine and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese has melted.
Serves 6 to 8.
Good with beef.

title: quick battered bluegills
directions: Rinse fillets and dip in dry pancake batter.
Then mix 2 cups pancake batter using milk in place of water.
For a thicker coating, use less milk.
Add remaining ingredients to pancake mix. Dip fillets in batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown. Number of servings varies.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk or beer, egg and oil in that order.
Dip chilled onion rings in batter and fry in deep fat.

title: tomato, sausage and eggplant soup
directions: Traditional layered salad enhanced with the taste of delicious hickory-smoked bacon.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the softened butter and shortening.
Add sugar and
then
eggs,
one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Sift together all dry ingredients; set aside. Add vanilla and milk together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla mixture to original mixture.
Bake in a greased and
floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350° and then 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: san francisco style cioppino(bon secour variation)
directions: In a 6 to
8-quart
pan
over medium heat, combine oil, onion, garlic, bell
pepper and parsley.
Cook, stirring often until onion is soft.
Stir in tomatoes (break up with a spoon) and their liquid, wine,
bay	leaf,
basil and oregano.
Cover and simmer until
slightly
thickened,
about 20 minutes.
To both, add clams (oysters), shrimp and crabs.
Cover and simmer gently until clams pop
open and shrimp turn pink (I hope the oysters pop open,
I don't know if they will or not), about 20 minutes.	Ladle
broth and
some of each shellfish into large soup bowls.	Serve
with French
bread.
It is good over rice too.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs,
oil,
sugar, flour and vanilla alternately. Add other ingredients.	Pour into two greased loaf pans or one oblong pan.
Bake until
loaf springs back when touched.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: vidalia onion pie casserole
directions: Slice onions and saute in margarine until limp but not brown. Add milk.
Cut off heat.
Place 1/2 of the onions in casserole. Sprinkle with cheese generously over onions.
Crumble crackers over cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Cut butter up on top and cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the best than anything cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
After taking out of oven, poke holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk all over cake; then add cream of coconut.
After cake is fully cooled, spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans over Cool Whip.

title: aunt brenda's mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain grease.
Add taco seasoning, onion, pepper and 2 cups of water.
Add tomatoes and let cook for about 30 minutes on medium heat.
After it thickens and the onion and pepper are done, add rice.
Stir and put in large casserole pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle cheese on top completely covering dish.
Cover and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix margarine into cracker crumbs and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and let stand a few minutes.
Take 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip and gently fold into mixture.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Top with more Cool Whip and crumbs.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Spread each piece meat with a teaspoon mustard; mix bacon, pickles and onion together in a small bowl.
Spoon along one end of each piece of meat.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion, and tie securely with string or fasten with toothpicks.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 2 pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add pie filling and pineapple (with juice). Stir in pecans. Mix well and congeal.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and cheese.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Top with bacon and mayonnaise mixture just before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix per directions.
Mix 1/2 cup pecans into batter and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil
chicken until tender and remove from bones.
Cook broccoli
for
minutes	(in
microwave	or
top of stove). Spread
chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put broccoli on top of
chicken.
Mix soups together with mayonnaise, 1/2 cup of milk
and cheese.
Pour this mixture on top of chicken and broccoli; put in oven until this begins to boil.
Take out and put your
dressing
that
you	have
mixed with your stick of melted margarine on top.
Put back in oven and cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put canned tomatoes into large cooking pot.
Add 1 quart water and salt-simmer.
In small boiler, put rice, macaroni and diced potato and cook until tender-drain.
In saucepan, saute ground beef and onion in vegetable oil until browned-drain.
Add all ingredients into cook pot.
Add corn and green beans and parsley. Simmer until thoroughly blended.
Serve with cornbread.
Can be frozen.
Other vegetables can be added if preferred.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend thoroughly with mixer.
Serve with apple slices or other fresh fruit.
Hint:
Low-fat cream cheese works equally well.
Dip apple slices in Sprite to keep them from turning brown.

title: quick cake
directions: Put together and beat in a mixing bowl cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in icing.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add water, eggs and pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cube steak and potatoes
directions: Fry cube steaks with oil in an electric frypan set at about 300°.
Lightly fry steaks.
Add onion and turn steaks.
Fry for about 10 minutes slowly.
Add sliced potatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Slow fry until potatoes are done, about 20 minutes. Add gravy (mix gravy as directed on package).
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: miracle soup
directions: Dice cabbage. Cook 8 minutes. Add diced onion and celery. Cook 5 minutes. Dice mangos and add to ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until desired tenderness of cabbage.
For dieters.

title: cheddar cheese chicken
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Shake chicken in mixture and cook each side about 15 minutes.
Add soup, onion, basil and water to chicken.
Cover and cook on low heat about 45 minutes or until done.

title: gooey squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Cook shrimp in boiling water until tender (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
Cook rice and put aside to cool.
Cook omelette.
Put aside to cool.
When cool, cut in strips.
Saute onions, green peppers and celery in oil.
Stir in rice, then the shrimp.
Shake in soy sauce, sprinkle in salt, pepper, garlic powder and any other seasoning you wish to put in.
Fold in the egg omelette, then fold in the scallions (spring onions, cut in small pieces but uncooked). Let the heat steam them.
Leave covered for about 1 to 2 minutes, then serve.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in 2 bread pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Take 2 cups of flour in bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, baking powder, soft butter and milk.
Add eggs; mix well.
Make a stiff dough, adding 1/2 cup flour.
With hands coated with flour, begin to knead.
Make large ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fingers.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil entire box of macaroni until done (put your salt in water).
Let drain real well.
Butter bottom of casserole pan (use size of lasagna pan).
Block cheese must be shredded very well. Layer small amount of macaroni and top with shredded cheese, followed by sliced Old English cheese.
Repeat this process, layering macaroni followed by cheese.

title: caramel pecan french toast
directions: Melt oleo in 8 or 9-inch pan; stir brown sugar into oleo and sprinkle with pecans.
Slightly beat egg; add milk.
Dip bread (both sides) in milk and lay on top of sugar and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; let stand in pan a minute or two.
Invert pan to remove.

title: chicken fricassee with rice
directions: Soak lemon juice with Greek seasoning.
Sear on high flame (to one side of grill).
Move to other side to cook with air holes open.

title: company potatoes
directions: Melt butter and mix with onion soup.
Add water and potatoes. Put in slow cooker and set on high.
If you use crock-pot, may take longer; estimated cooking time is 3 hours.
You should stir frequently.

title: rolls or bread
directions: Pour over this 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until lard melts. Add 1 cup cold water.
Add 1 cup lukewarm water with 1 package dry yeast dissolved in it.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Knead a little and put in a bowl to raise.
You can put in refrigerator to raise if you want.
Punch down and make into bread or rolls to raise again until double.
Bake bread at 350° or rolls at 400°.
Makes 3 loaves or lots of rolls.

title: squash casserole 3
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Top with Pepperidge Farm crumbs. Cook 1 hour at 300° to 350°.

title: red velvet cake and icing
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda three times.
Mix cocoa, food coloring and vinegar together.
Add egg and sugar mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix alternately with buttermilk, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat well. Bake in three layers at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together lightly.
Make one day in advance.

title: hot five bean salad
directions: *Any combination of kidney beans, green beans, great northern beans, lima beans, wax beans, black eyed peas, or garbanzo beans may be used.

title: quick party mix
directions: Pour first 5 ingredients in a large Tupperware bowl (with a lid) or a large brown grocery bag.
Mix in a measuring cup: spices, oil and Hidden Valley Ranch mix.
Pour over cereal mixture and shake (and shake and shake).
Store in airtight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Save small amount of beef. Form into a ball and roll in extra chopped beef.
Chill.

title: ground turkey corn casserole
directions: In a frying pan over medium heat, cook ground turkey with garlic.
Cook elbows according to package directions.
Drain. Pour cooked elbows into deep 3-quart casserole dish.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bulgarian apple cake("you don't have to peel the apples!")
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil. Sift flour, soda and salt. Add to first mixture and beat well. Stir in apples and nuts. Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Combine onions, garlic, ground beef and olive oil in pressure pan.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Heat to 15 pounds pressure. Cook 20 minutes.
Reduce pressure under cold water.
Serve over spaghetti.
I do mine in slow cooker.
Cook part of the day.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil, without stirring, over moderate heat 9 to 10 minutes to 238° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour (until cold).
Add vanilla and beat quickly to no-gloss and until it will hold its shape. Stir in nuts and cherries and turn onto oiled or buttered pan. Makes 2 pounds.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Melt butter.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper.
Add frozen broccoli and salt and pepper; steam a little while.
Add Cheez Whiz, rice and soup; let melt.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Slow cook 1/2 hour.

title: surprise cake(deb made it!!!)
directions: Pound the daylights out of the box of vanilla wafers! They all have to become dust.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: In shallow dish, beat egg.
Dip chicken into egg; on waxed paper, coat chicken with bread crumbs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet, heat spaghetti sauce to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Cover; cook until cheese is melted. Serve with spaghetti.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Cut bacon into 3 equal sections. Wrap a piece of bacon around each Little Smokie, securing with a toothpick. Place them in a crock pot and cover with brown sugar. Heat on high 3 to 4 hours. The brown sugar, bacon and smokies will make the sauce as they heat. Do not add any liquids.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter with the sugar; add eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder and vanilla; mix well.
Spread half of dough in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Cover with rows of apple slices; top with remainder of dough and spread as well as possible.
Dough is soft and will cover apples while baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and spread with thin icing.

title: easy manicotti with cheese
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce with water to boil.
Reduce and simmer. Mix cheeses together with parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon into uncooked manicotti.
Pour 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange filled manicotti in single layer over sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and onion.
Gradually beat in milk or water and egg.
Allow to sit 5 minutes.
Drop from spoon into hot fat where fish was fried.
Fry until golden brown; drain on absorbent paper.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Finely chop the cabbage, green peppers, onions and olives and place them in a large bowl.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and cocoa; add dry ingredients with sour milk.
Beat until smooth.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add, and mix well (thin batter).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: continental chicken casserole
directions: Make sauce of butter, flour, broth and cream.
Cook over medium flame until thick, stirring constantly. Combine all seasonings and blend into sauce.
Stir in wine. Fold in eggs and chicken.
Turn into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parsnips in broth
directions: Combine the parsnips, garlic and 1/4 cup broth in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until the parsnips are slightly tender.
Stir in the remaining 1 3/4 cups broth, cilantro or parsley, cayenne and black pepper. Cover again and cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes, or until heated through.

title: fish baked in herb sauce
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Saute onion and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, thyme and minced parsley and bring to a boil.
Add sauce to fish and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until fish flakes easily.

title: chicken intrigue
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a single layer in shallow baking dish or casserole dish.
Combine ingredients.
Blend well.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Sauce is excellent served over rice.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine and cold water.
Add boiling water; stir. Add pineapple with juice, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well together and let almost set in refrigerator.
Tear up in bite size pieces the angel food cake.
Mix together with gelatine mixture and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread in pan and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: ham with orange sauce(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients (except ham) in 1 cup glass measuring cup.
Mix well.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring once.
Set aside. Arrange ham in shallow microwave-safe serving dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until just about hot.
Spoon on enough sauce to glaze ham.
Cover. Microwave (High) 1 to 2 minutes, or until heated through.
Serve remaining sauce with ham.

title: beef and veggie soft taco
directions: Brown beef with taco seasoning.
Add salsa and frozen veggies. Simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add half of the cheese. Put mixture in tortillas.
Roll.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan, seam down.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain if too much liquid.
Cool.
Saute chopped vegetables in small amount of oleo or Pam but not brown.
Beat egg whites until soft peak forms.
Add all ingredients to squash except crumbs.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Spread buttered bread crumbs on top and bake until lightly browned.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add oil and beat.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, crushed pineapple and carrots.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients; add to zucchini mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna muffin melt
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise, onion, celery and green pepper. Spread mixture on muffin halves and place under broiler for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cheese slices and return to broiler for an additional 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound the chicken breasts until flat; saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
When veggies are done, put a spoonful of mix on each chicken breast.
Place 2 small pieces of butter inside and sprinkle of cheese.
Roll together; hold together with toothpicks. Roll in egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry the chicken.
Serve with noodles.

title: pilgrim pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for a double crust pie.
Break egg white with fork until frothy (DO NOT beat).
Add cream, sugar and salt. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell; cover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: old fashion beef vegetable soup
directions: Flour, salt and pepper roast and saute in oil, then bake roast until done.
Place all drippings.
Roast in large deep pan.
Add 2 cups water, cabbage, carrots, onion and potatoes.
Cook on medium to low heat until vegetables are done.
Add corn, peas, 1 can tomato and juice, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, simmering, for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately or keep refrigerated and serve later.

title: mrs. murray strawberry short cake(recipe is close to 100 years old.)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add shortening.
Add slightly beaten egg, vanilla and milk.
Dough will be stiff.
Spread over greased pans.
This recipe will make 4 (8-inch) pie pans or 3 (9-inch) pie pans.
Cakes are thin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cake is done, melt 2 tablespoons margarine or butter.
Brush each cake with margarine or butter.
Pour sweetened strawberries over each layer as they are assembled in layers.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to batter; mix well.
Roll out and cut out shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen strawberries; break apart with a fork.
Add remaining fruit.
Put half of mixture in mold. When set, spread on sour cream.
Put remaining jello mixture on top.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Put together and cook slow 40 minutes. Put in jars. Hot water bath 10 minutes. Makes 6 pints.

title: finger paint
directions: Put dry
starch in saucepan.
Gradually add cold water, stirring until smooth. Add the boiling water, stirring rapidly and continually.
Add
the
detergent
and
stir
again
until smooth. (There is	no need to cook this recipe.) May add food coloring for color.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Toast English muffins.
Spoon tomato sauce on tops.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Top with shredded Mozzarella. Place in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: microwave tetrazzini
directions: Combine onion, pepper and oil.
Cook Full power 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook Full power another 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil for one minute. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop into balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Place in fridge overnight.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add eggs.
Beat for two minutes.
Sift all dry ingredients and alternately add with buttermilk to the egg mixture.
Mix in all nuts and prunes.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Dissolve drink mix in water and refrigerate until needed. Chill sugar-free pop.
Place in punch bowl along with a chunk of ice or make an ice ring from some of the drink mix.
Add pop to remainder of drink mix in bowl.
Mix lightly and serve.
To add a special touch, add a few grapes or strawberries to the ice ring. This is a free food.

title: ski slope soup
directions: Cook all ingredients 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: banana fudge-walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of an 8-inch square pan.
Melt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, the margarine or butter and chocolate chips.
Beat in thoroughly with a spoon the remaining ingredients.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Makes 16 brownies.
Very delicious.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Combine oil, bananas, eggs, vanilla, Bisquick and sugar in mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed for 30 seconds.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well except crackers and butter. Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tomato relish
directions: Dice tomatoes and let drain while chopping other ingredients. Mix all ingredients and stew for 30 minutes.
Put in jars.
Put lids on tight.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 1 year.
Good!

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
Punch holes all over cake. Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand and pour over cake.
Cool cake and put on Cool Whip.

title: lamb shanks, italian style
directions: Using paper toweling, blot the lamb shanks dry. Heat the oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven or flameproof casserole over moderate heat for 1 minute. Add the shanks and brown well on all sides 10 minutes. Remove the shanks and set aside. Add the shallots and garlic to the Dutch oven and saut, stirring frequently until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the green peppers and saut, stirring occasionally until soft, about 5 minutes more. Stir in white wine, scraping up any browned bits on the bottom of the pan. Return the shanks to the pan. Add the tomatoes, rosemary, salt, pepper and stock. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer, turning and basting the shanks occasionally with pan juices, until tender, 1 1/2 hours. Skim excess fat. Add the orzo; cover and simmer until tender, 10 minutes. Stir in all but 2 tablespoons of the parsley and sprinkle the remainder on top. Serves 4.

title: lover's chicken
directions: In a skillet, slowly brown chicken pieces in butter for about 25	minutes.
Combine
remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and cook over
low	heat
about
minutes
or until chicken is done.
Stir frequently.
Serve over rice.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until tender; add salt before boiling.
Butter baking dish.
Make layers of cabbage and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle a little sugar and pepper.
Add a few squares of butter.
Add another layer of the same order.
Add layers until the amount is reached.
Pour enough hot milk in to cover layers.
Bake at 375° until thick and brown on top, 45 minutes. Good served with pork.

title: ding bats
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in 4 cups Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and roll in flaked coconut.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine; gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts, mixing just until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and frost with a caramel frosting or sift confectioners sugar over cooled cake.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions; cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain; cover again with boiling water and let come to a boil.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain; put all together and seal while hot.

title: broccoli salad 2
directions: Mix everything together except bacon and nuts; refrigerate.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, cheese and mayonnaise together.
Put in flat casserole.
Sprinkle bacon pieces on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt jo's ice cream
directions: Whip egg whites with 3/4 cup sugar until stiff.
In separate bowl, whip egg yolks with 3/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Whip whipping cream until firm.
Pour all 3 mixtures into freezer with 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 1 cup fresh fruits of choice; fill freezer to fill line with milk and freeze.

title: eli slocomb's oyster casserole("yankee style")
directions: Take rolling pin to crackers (if this won't make them behave, use food processor).
Make lumpy crumbs.
Save some crumbs for top. Beat eggs into absolute submission, using fork or switch.
Mix eggs, crackers and oysters together in lightly greased 4-quart casserole.
Add a "bit" of pepper and a "smidge" of salt. Refrigerate for 3 hours, then begin baking process.

title: chilled watercress soup
directions: Blend undiluted soup and watercress in blender at low speed. In saucepan over medium heat, heat mixture with milk and basil. Do not let boil.
Refrigerate.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: With a mixer, beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. On low speed, add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in whipping cream at low speed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frosted creams
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Frost with any white frosting.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order listed. Can well serve as a one-dish meal.

title: maply appetizers
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Cut sausages in thirds crosswise; brown in skillet.
Blend cornstarch, salt, reserved pineapple syrup, maple syrup, water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple, sausage, pepper and cherries. Cook 5 minutes.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Spear with cocktail picks.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into glass loaf pan. Freeze at least three hours or until firm. Thirty minutes before serving, remove from freezer to refrigerator.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook carrots, onion and celery in butter.
Stir in flour, add salt and broth.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in milk and add cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Do not allow soup to boil.

title: chicken fajitas on the grill
directions: In shallow dish, combine first 10 ingredients; mix well.
Add chicken breasts; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain chicken; reserve marinade.
Grill chicken on covered grill, basting often with marinade, until done, approximately 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, shortening, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch drops
directions: Melt morsels over hot
water.
Stir in noodles and nuts until well coated.
Drop
by
spoonfuls on waxed paper and let cool.

title: anne's flank steak
directions: Take flank steak and sprinkle lightly with meat tenderizer. Season steak with garlic salt or lemon pepper.
Place diced onion and pepper in middle of steak.
Roll steak in a jelly roll shape. Secure with toothpicks.
Take bacon and wrap around steak until completely covered.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place steak on grill. Cook for 7 minutes on each side for a total of 28 minutes for medium.
Remove from grill and cut like a jelly roll.
Garnish with fresh mushrooms or parsley.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti until soft (as directed on package).
Set aside. Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add stewed tomatoes or tomato juice, tomato sauce, chili powder and herb package mix to hamburger and onion.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Layer spaghetti and sauce in a 2-quart casserole dish, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese from Kraft dinner.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken breast with rice
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Grease dish with margarine.
Spread rice over dish, chicken next.
Mix can of soup with water and pour over.
Add mushrooms on top and sprinkle dry soup over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: yankee doodle noodle
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix spaghetti sauce, cooked macaroni, Ricotta cheese and cream cheese, put into a baking dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: lemon cake top pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and butter.
Add egg yolks, lemon juice and milk; mix well.
Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie shell, which has been baked 5 minutes at 425°.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 tomato sauce.
Form into loaf.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple mold
directions: Place cinnamon candies and hot water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat
until candies are dissolved.
Dissolve jello and dash of salt in hot liquid.
Add applesauce.
Chill until firm.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Pour melted margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan, making sure sides of pan are greased.
Layer other ingredients in order. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares. Makes 2 dozen.
